  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ezekiel\u2019s Vision of God"
      title: "Ezekiel\u2019s Vision of God"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the thirtieth year, in the fourth month, on
        the fifth day of the month, as I was among the captives by the River Chebar,
        that  the heavens were opened and I saw visions of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "On the fifth day of the month, which was in the fifth year of King
        Jehoiachin\u2019s captivity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: the word of the Lord came expressly to Ezekiel the priest, the son
        of Buzi, in the land of the Chaldeans by the River Chebar; and the hand of
        the Lord was upon him there.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then I looked, and behold, a whirlwind was coming out of the north,
        a great cloud with raging fire engulfing itself; and brightness was all around
        it and radiating out of its midst like the color of amber, out of the midst
        of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also from within it came the likeness of four living creatures. And
        this was their appearance: they had the likeness of a man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Each one had four faces, and each one had four wings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Their legs were straight, and the soles of their feet were like the
        soles of calves\u2019 feet. They sparkled like the color of burnished bronze. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The hands of a man were under their wings on their four sides; and
        each of the four had faces and wings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Their wings touched one another. The  creatures did not turn when
        they went, but each one went straight forward.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As for the likeness of their faces, each  had the face of a man;
        each of the four had the face of a lion on the right side, each of the four
        had the face of an ox on the left side, and each of the four had the face
        of an eagle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Thus were their faces. Their wings stretched upward; two wings of
        each one touched one another, and two covered their bodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And each one went straight forward; they went wherever the spirit
        wanted to go, and they did not turn when they went.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As for the likeness of the living creatures, their appearance was
        like burning coals of fire, like the appearance of torches going back and
        forth among the living creatures. The fire was bright, and out of the fire
        went lightning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And the living creatures ran back and forth, in appearance like a
        flash of lightning.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now as I looked at the living creatures, behold, a wheel was on the
        earth beside each living creature with its four faces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The appearance of the wheels and their workings was  like the color
        of beryl, and all four had the same likeness. The appearance of their workings
        was, as it were, a wheel in the middle of a wheel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When they moved, they went toward any one of four directions; they
        did not turn aside when they went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As for their rims, they were so high they were awesome; and their
        rims were  full of eyes, all around the four of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When the living creatures went, the wheels went beside them; and
        when the living creatures were lifted up from the earth, the wheels were
        lifted up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Wherever the spirit wanted to go, they went, because there the spirit
        went; and the wheels were lifted together with them, for the spirit of the
        living creatures was in the wheels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: When those went, these went; when those stood, these stood; and when
        those were lifted up from the earth, the wheels were lifted up together with
        them, for the spirit of the living creatures was in the wheels.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The likeness of the firmament above the heads of the living creatures
        was like the color of an awesome crystal, stretched out over their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And under the firmament their wings spread  out straight, one toward
        another. Each one had two which covered one side, and each one had two which
        covered the other side of the body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When they went, I heard the noise of their wings, like the noise
        of many waters, like the voice of the Almighty, a tumult like the noise of
        an army; and when they stood still, they let down their wings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: A voice came from above the firmament that was over their heads; whenever
        they stood, they let down their wings.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And above the firmament over their heads was the likeness of a throne,
        in appearance like a sapphire stone; on the likeness of the throne was a
        likeness with the appearance of a man high above it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Also from the appearance of His waist and upward I saw, as it were,
        the color of amber with the appearance of fire all around within it; and
        from the appearance of His waist and downward I saw, as it were, the appearance
        of fire with brightness all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Ezekiel Sent to Rebellious Israel'
      title: Ezekiel Sent to Rebellious Israel
      number: 28
      content: Like the appearance of a rainbow in a cloud on a rainy day, so was
        the appearance of the brightness all around it. This was the appearance of
        the likeness of the glory of the Lord.So when I saw it,  I fell on my face,
        and I heard a voice of One speaking.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CSon of man, stand on your feet, and I will
        speak to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the Spirit entered me when He spoke to me, and set me on my
        feet; and I heard Him who spoke to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And He said to me: \u201CSon of man, I am sending you to the children
        of Israel, to a rebellious nation that has rebelled against Me; they and
        their fathers have transgressed against Me to this very day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For they  are impudent and stubborn children. I am sending you to
        them, and you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "As for them, whether they hear or whether they refuse\u2014for they
        are a rebellious house\u2014yet they will know that a prophet has been among
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, do not be afraid of them nor be afraid
        of their words, though briers and thorns are with you and you dwell among
        scorpions; do not be afraid of their words or dismayed by their looks, though
        they are a rebellious house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall speak My words to them, whether they hear or whether they
        refuse, for they are rebellious. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But you, son of man, hear what I say to you. Do not be rebellious
        like that rebellious house; open your mouth and eat what I give you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now when I looked, there was a hand stretched out to me; and behold,
        a scroll of a book was in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then He spread it before me; and there  was writing on the inside
        and on the outside, and written on it were lamentations and mourning and
        woe.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Moreover He said to me, \u201CSon of man, eat what you find; eat
        this scroll, and go, speak to the house of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So I opened my mouth, and He caused me to eat that scroll.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CSon of man, feed your belly, and fill your
        stomach with this scroll that I give you.\u201D So I ate, and it was in my
        mouth like honey in sweetness."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then He said to me: \u201CSon of man, go to the house of Israel and
        speak with My words to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For you are not sent to a people of unfamiliar speech and of hard
        language, but to the house of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'not to many people of unfamiliar speech and of hard language, whose
        words you cannot understand. Surely, had I sent you to them, they would have
        listened to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the house of Israel will not listen to you, because they will
        not listen to Me; for all the house of Israel are impudent and hard-hearted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behold, I have made your face strong against their faces, and your
        forehead strong against their foreheads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Like adamant stone, harder than flint, I have made your forehead;
        do not be afraid of them, nor be dismayed at their looks, though they are
        a rebellious house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Moreover He said to me: \u201CSon of man, receive into your heart
        all My words that I speak to you, and hear with your ears. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And go, get to the captives, to the children of your people, and
        speak to them and tell them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God,\u2019 whether
        they hear, or whether they refuse.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Spirit lifted me up, and I heard behind me a great thunderous
        voice: \u201CBlessed is the glory of the Lord from His place!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I also heard the noise of the wings of the living creatures that
        touched one another, and the noise of the wheels beside them, and a great
        thunderous noise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the Spirit lifted me up and took me away, and I went in bitterness,
        in the heat of my spirit; but the hand of the Lord was strong upon me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Ezekiel Is a Watchman'
      title: Ezekiel Is a Watchman
      number: 15
      content: Then I came to the captives at Tel Abib, who dwelt by the River Chebar;
        and I sat where they sat, and remained there astonished among them seven
        days.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now it came to pass at the end of seven days that the word of the
        Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CSon of man, I have made you a watchman for the house of Israel;
        therefore hear a word from My mouth, and give them warning from Me: "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When I say to the wicked, \u2018You shall surely die,\u2019 and you
        give him no warning, nor speak to warn the wicked from his wicked way, to
        save his life, that same wicked man  shall die in his iniquity; but his blood
        I will require at your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yet, if you warn the wicked, and he does not turn from his wickedness,
        nor from his wicked way, he shall die in his iniquity; but you have delivered
        your soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAgain, when a righteous man turns from his righteousness and
        commits iniquity, and I lay a stumbling block before him, he shall die; because
        you did not give him warning, he shall die in his sin, and his righteousness
        which he has done shall not be remembered; but his blood I will require at
        your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Nevertheless if you warn the righteous man that the righteous should
        not sin, and he does not sin, he shall surely live because he took warning;
        also you will have delivered your soul.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the hand of the Lord was upon me there, and He said to me, \u201CArise,
        go out into the plain, and there I shall talk with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So I arose and went out into the plain, and behold, the glory of
        the Lord stood there, like the glory which I saw by the River Chebar; and
        I fell on my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the Spirit entered me and set me on my feet, and spoke with
        me and said to me: \u201CGo, shut yourself inside your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And you, O son of man, surely they will put ropes on you and bind
        you with them, so that you cannot go out among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will make your tongue cling to the roof of your mouth, so that
        you shall be mute and not be one to rebuke them, for they are a rebellious
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But when I speak with you, I will open your mouth, and you shall
        say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God.\u2019 He who hears, let him hear;
        and he who refuses, let him refuse; for they are a rebellious house."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Siege of Jerusalem Portrayed'
      title: The Siege of Jerusalem Portrayed
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CYou also, son of man, take a clay tablet and lay it before
        you, and portray on it a city, Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Lay siege against it, build a siege wall against it, and heap up
        a mound against it; set camps against it also, and place battering rams against
        it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Moreover take for yourself an iron plate, and set it as an iron wall
        between you and the city. Set your face against it, and it shall be besieged,
        and you shall lay siege against it. This will  be a sign to the house of
        Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLie also on your left side, and lay the iniquity of the house
        of Israel upon it. According to the number of the days that you lie on it,
        you shall bear their iniquity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For I have laid on you the years of their iniquity, according to
        the number of the days, three hundred and ninety days; so you shall bear
        the iniquity of the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And when you have completed them, lie again on your right side; then
        you shall bear the iniquity of the house of Judah forty days. I have laid
        on you a day for each year.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CTherefore you shall set your face toward the siege of Jerusalem;
        your arm shall  be uncovered, and you shall prophesy against it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And surely I will restrain you so that you cannot turn from one side
        to another till you have ended the days of your siege.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAlso take for yourself wheat, barley, beans, lentils, millet,
        and spelt; put them into one vessel, and make bread of them for yourself.
        During the number of days that you lie on your side, three hundred and ninety
        days, you shall eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And your food which you eat shall  be by weight, twenty shekels a
        day; from time to time you shall eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall also drink water by measure, one-sixth of a hin; from time
        to time you shall drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And you shall eat it as barley cakes; and bake it using fuel of human
        waste in their sight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CSo shall the children of Israel eat their
        defiled bread among the Gentiles, where I will drive them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So I said, \u201CAh, Lord God! Indeed I have never defiled myself
        from my youth till now; I have never eaten what died of itself or was torn
        by beasts, nor has abominable flesh ever come into my mouth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CSee, I am giving you cow dung instead of
        human waste, and you shall prepare your bread over it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Moreover He said to me, \u201CSon of man, surely I will cut off the
        supply of bread in Jerusalem; they shall eat bread by weight and with anxiety,
        and shall drink water by measure and with dread, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: that they may lack bread and water, and be dismayed with one another,
        and waste away because of their iniquity.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Sword Against Jerusalem'
      title: A Sword Against Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, take a sharp sword, take it as a barber\u2019s
        razor, and pass it over your head and your beard; then take scales to weigh
        and divide the hair. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall burn with fire one-third in the midst of the city, when
        the days of the siege are finished; then you shall take one-third and strike
        around it with the sword, and one-third you shall scatter in the wind: I
        will draw out a sword after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall also take a small number of them and bind them in the edge
        of your garment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Then take some of them again and throw them into the midst of the
        fire, and burn them in the fire. From there a fire will go out into all the
        house of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God: \u2018This is Jerusalem; I have set
        her in the midst of the nations and the countries all around her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "She has rebelled against My judgments by doing wickedness more than
        the nations, and against My statutes more than the countries that are all
        around her; for they have refused My judgments, and they have not walked
        in My statutes.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Because you have multiplied
        disobedience more than the nations that are all around you, have not walked
        in My statutes nor kept My judgments, nor even done according to the judgments
        of the nations that are all around you\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Indeed I, even I, am against
        you and will execute judgments in your midst in the sight of the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will do among you what I have never done, and the like of which
        I will never do again, because of all your abominations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Therefore fathers shall eat their sons in your midst, and sons shall
        eat their fathers; and I will execute judgments among you, and all of you
        who remain I will scatter to all the winds.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018Therefore, as I live,\u2019 says the Lord God, \u2018surely,
        because you have defiled My sanctuary with all your detestable things and
        with all your abominations, therefore I will also diminish you;  My eye will
        not spare, nor will I have any pity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: One-third of you shall die of the pestilence, and be consumed with
        famine in your midst; and one-third shall fall by the sword all around you;
        and I will scatter another third to all the winds, and I will draw out a
        sword after them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Thus shall My anger be spent, and I will cause My fury to rest
        upon them, and I will be avenged; and they shall know that I, the Lord, have
        spoken it in My zeal, when I have spent My fury upon them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Moreover I will make you a waste and a reproach among the nations
        that are all around you, in the sight of all who pass by.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u2018So it shall be a reproach, a taunt, a lesson, and an astonishment
        to the nations that are all around you, when I execute judgments among you
        in anger and in fury and in furious rebukes. I, the Lord, have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When I send against them the terrible arrows of famine which shall
        be for destruction, which I will send to destroy you, I will increase the
        famine upon you and cut off your supply of bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I will send against you famine and wild beasts, and they will
        bereave you. Pestilence and blood shall pass through you, and I will bring
        the sword against you. I, the Lord, have spoken.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Idolatrous Israel'
      title: Judgment on Idolatrous Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face toward the mountains of Israel, and
        prophesy against them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018O mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord God!
        Thus says the Lord God to the mountains, to the hills, to the ravines, and
        to the valleys: \u201CIndeed I, even I, will bring a sword against you, and
        I will destroy your high places. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then your altars shall be desolate, your incense altars shall be
        broken, and I will cast down your slain men before your idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I will lay the corpses of the children of Israel before their
        idols, and I will scatter your bones all around your altars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In all your dwelling places the cities shall be laid waste, and the
        high places shall be desolate, so that your altars may be laid waste and
        made desolate, your idols may be broken and made to cease, your incense altars
        may be cut down, and your works may be abolished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The slain shall fall in your midst, and you shall know that I am the
        Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYet I will leave a remnant, so that you may have some who escape
        the sword among the nations, when you are scattered through the countries. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then those of you who escape will remember Me among the nations where
        they are carried captive, because I was crushed by their adulterous heart
        which has departed from Me, and by their eyes which play the harlot after
        their idols; they will loathe themselves for the evils which they committed
        in all their abominations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they shall know that I am the Lord; I have not said in vain that
        I would bring this calamity upon them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CPound your fists and stamp your
        feet, and say, \u2018Alas, for all the evil abominations of the house of
        Israel! For they shall fall by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He who is far off shall die by the pestilence, he who is near shall
        fall by the sword, and he who remains and is besieged shall die by the famine.
        Thus will I spend My fury upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you shall know that I am the Lord, when their slain are among
        their idols all around their altars, on every high hill, on all the mountaintops,
        under every green tree, and under every thick oak, wherever they offered
        sweet incense to all their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So I will stretch out My hand against them and make the land desolate,
        yes, more desolate than the wilderness toward Diblah, in all their dwelling
        places. Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u2019 \u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Israel Is Near'
      title: Judgment on Israel Is Near
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, thus says the Lord God to the land of
        Israel:\u2018An end! The end has come upon the four corners of the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Now the end has  come upon you,And I will send My anger against you;I
        will judge you according to your ways,And I will repay you for all your abominations.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "My eye will not spare you,Nor will I have pity;But I will repay your
        ways,And your abominations will be in your midst;Then you shall know that
        I am the Lord!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God:\u2018A disaster, a singular disaster;Behold,
        it has come!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: An end has come,The end has come;It has dawned for you;Behold, it
        has come!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Doom has come to you, you who dwell in the land;The time has come,A
        day of trouble is near,And not of rejoicing in the mountains.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now upon you I will soon pour out My fury,And spend My anger upon
        you;I will judge you according to your ways,And I will repay you for all
        your abominations.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018My eye will not spare,Nor will I have pity;I will repay you
        according to your ways,And your abominations will be in your midst.Then you
        shall know that I am the Lord who strikes."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Behold, the day!Behold, it has come!Doom has gone out;The rod
        has blossomed,Pride has budded."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Violence has risen up into a rod of wickedness;None of them shall 
        remain,None of their multitude,None of them;Nor shall  there  be wailing
        for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The time has come,The day draws near.\u2018Let not the buyer rejoice,Nor
        the seller mourn,For wrath is on their whole multitude."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For the seller shall not return to what has been sold,Though he may
        still be alive;For the vision concerns the whole multitude,And it shall not
        turn back;No one will strengthen himselfWho lives in iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018They have blown the trumpet and made everyone ready,But no
        one goes to battle;For My wrath is on all their multitude."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The sword is outside,And the pestilence and famine within.Whoever
        is in the fieldWill die by the sword;And whoever is in the city,Famine and
        pestilence will devour him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Those who survive will escape and be on the mountainsLike doves
        of the valleys,All of them mourning,Each for his iniquity."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Every hand will be feeble,And every knee will be as weak as water.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They will also be girded with sackcloth;Horror will cover them;Shame
        will  be on every face,Baldness on all their heads.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018They will throw their silver into the streets,And their gold
        will be like refuse;Their silver and their gold will not be able to deliver
        themIn the day of the wrath of the Lord;They will not satisfy their souls,Nor
        fill their stomachs,Because it became their stumbling block of iniquity."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018As for the beauty of his ornaments,He set it in majesty;But
        they made from itThe images of their abominations\u2014Their detestable things;Therefore
        I have made itLike refuse to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will give it as plunderInto the hands of strangers,And to the wicked
        of the earth as spoil;And they shall defile it.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: I will turn My face from them,And they will defile My secret place;For
        robbers shall enter it and defile it.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018Make a chain,For the land is filled with crimes of blood,And
        the city is full of violence."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Therefore I will bring the worst of the Gentiles,And they will possess
        their houses;I will cause the pomp of the strong to cease,And their holy
        places shall be defiled.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Destruction comes;They will seek peace, but there  shall  be none.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Disaster will come upon disaster,And rumor will be upon rumor.Then
        they will seek a vision from a prophet;But the law will perish from the priest,And
        counsel from the elders.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018The king will mourn,The prince will be clothed with desolation,And
        the hands of the common people will tremble.I will do to them according to
        their way,And according to what they deserve I will judge them;Then they
        shall know that I am the Lord!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abominations in the Temple'
      title: Abominations in the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in the sixth year, in the sixth month, on the
        fifth day of the month, as I sat in my house with the elders of Judah sitting
        before me, that the hand of the Lord God fell upon me there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then I looked, and there was a likeness, like the appearance of fire\u2014from
        the appearance of His waist and downward, fire; and from His waist and upward,
        like the appearance of brightness, like the color of amber. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He stretched out the form of a hand, and took me by a lock of my
        hair; and the Spirit lifted me up between earth and heaven, and brought me
        in visions of God to Jerusalem, to the door of the north gate of the inner
        court,  where the seat of the image of jealousy was, which provokes to jealousy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And behold, the glory of the God of Israel was there, like the vision
        that I saw in the plain.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CSon of man, lift your eyes now toward the
        north.\u201D So I lifted my eyes toward the north, and there, north of the
        altar gate, was this image of jealousy in the entrance."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Furthermore He said to me, \u201CSon of man, do you see what they
        are doing, the great abominations that the house of Israel commits here,
        to make Me go far away from My sanctuary? Now turn again, you will see greater
        abominations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So He brought me to the door of the court; and when I looked, there
        was a hole in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CSon of man, dig into the wall\u201D; and
        when I dug into the wall, there was a door."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CGo in, and see the wicked abominations which
        they are doing there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I went in and saw, and there\u2014every sort of creeping thing,
        abominable beasts, and all the idols of the house of Israel, portrayed all
        around on the walls. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And there stood before them seventy men of the elders of the house
        of Israel, and in their midst stood Jaazaniah the son of Shaphan. Each man
        had a censer in his hand, and a thick cloud of incense went up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CSon of man, have you seen what the elders
        of the house of Israel do in the dark, every man in the room of his idols?
        For they say, \u2018The Lord does not see us, the Lord has forsaken the land.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CTurn again, and you will see greater abominations
        that they are doing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So He brought me to the door of the north gate of the Lord\u2019s
        house; and to my dismay, women were sitting there weeping for Tammuz."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CHave you seen this, O son of man? Turn
        again, you will see greater abominations than these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So He brought me into the inner court of the Lord\u2019s house; and
        there, at the door of the temple of the Lord, between the porch and the altar,
        were about twenty-five men with their backs toward the temple of the Lord
        and their faces toward the east, and they were worshiping the sun toward
        the east."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CHave you seen this, O son of man? Is it
        a trivial thing to the house of Judah to commit the abominations which they
        commit here? For they have filled the land with violence; then they have
        returned to provoke Me to anger. Indeed they put the branch to their nose. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore I also will act in fury. My eye will not spare nor will
        I have pity; and though they cry in My ears with a loud voice, I will not
        hear them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wicked Are Slain'
      title: The Wicked Are Slain
      number: 1
      content: "Then He called out in my hearing with a loud voice, saying, \u201CLet
        those who have charge over the city draw near, each with a deadly weapon
        in his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And suddenly six men came from the direction of the upper gate, which
        faces north, each with his battle-ax in his hand. One man among them was
        clothed with linen and had a writer\u2019s inkhorn at his side. They went
        in and stood beside the bronze altar."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the glory of the God of Israel had gone up from the cherub, where
        it had been, to the threshold of the temple. And He called to the man clothed
        with linen, who had the writer\u2019s inkhorn at his side; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and the Lord said to him, \u201CGo through the midst of the city,
        through the midst of Jerusalem, and put a mark on the foreheads of the men
        who sigh and cry over all the abominations that are done within it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "To the others He said in my hearing, \u201CGo after him through the
        city and kill; do not let your eye spare, nor have any pity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Utterly slay old and young men, maidens and little children and women;
        but do not come near anyone on whom is the mark; and begin at My sanctuary.\u201D
        So they began with the elders who were before the temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then He said to them, \u201CDefile the temple, and fill the courts
        with the slain. Go out!\u201D And they went out and killed in the city."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So it was, that while they were killing them, I was left alone; and
        I fell on my face and cried out, and said, \u201CAh, Lord God! Will You destroy
        all the remnant of Israel in pouring out Your fury on Jerusalem?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CThe iniquity of the house of Israel and
        Judah is exceedingly great, and the land is full of bloodshed, and the city
        full of perversity; for they say, \u2018The Lord has forsaken the land, and
        the Lord does not see!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And as for Me also, My eye will neither spare, nor will I have pity,
        but  I will recompense their deeds on their own head.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Just then, the man clothed with linen, who had the inkhorn at his
        side, reported back and said, \u201CI have done as You commanded me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Glory Departs from the Temple'
      title: The Glory Departs from the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'And I looked, and there in the firmament that was above the head
        of the cherubim, there appeared something like a sapphire stone, having the
        appearance of the likeness of a throne. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then He spoke to the man clothed with linen, and said, \u201CGo in
        among the wheels, under the cherub, fill your hands with coals of fire from
        among the cherubim, and scatter them over the city.\u201D And he went in
        as I watched."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the cherubim were standing on the south side of the temple when
        the man went in, and the cloud filled the inner court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the glory of the Lord went up from the cherub, and  paused over
        the threshold of the temple; and the house was filled with the cloud, and
        the court was full of the brightness of the Lord\u2019s glory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And the sound of the wings of the cherubim was heard even in the outer
        court, like the voice of Almighty God when He speaks.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then it happened, when He commanded the man clothed in linen, saying,
        \u201CTake fire from among the wheels, from among the cherubim,\u201D that
        he went in and stood beside the wheels. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the cherub stretched out his hand from among the cherubim to
        the fire that was among the cherubim, and took some  of  it and put it into
        the hands of the man clothed with linen, who took it and went out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The cherubim appeared to have the form of a man\u2019s hand under
        their wings."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when I looked, there were four wheels by the cherubim, one wheel
        by one cherub and another wheel by each other cherub; the wheels appeared
        to  have the color of a beryl stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As  for their appearance, all four looked alike\u2014as it were,
        a wheel in the middle of a wheel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When they went, they went toward any  of their four directions; they
        did not turn aside when they went, but followed in the direction the head
        was facing. They did not turn aside when they went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And their whole body, with their back, their hands, their wings,
        and the wheels that the four had, were  full of eyes all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As for the wheels, they were called in my hearing, \u201CWheel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Each one had four faces: the first face was the face of a cherub,
        the second face the face of a man, the third the face of a lion, and the
        fourth the face of an eagle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the cherubim were lifted up. This was  the living creature I
        saw by the River Chebar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When the cherubim went, the wheels went beside them; and when the
        cherubim lifted their wings to mount up from the earth, the same wheels also
        did not turn from beside them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: When the  cherubim stood still, the  wheels stood still, and when
        one was lifted up, the  other lifted itself up, for the spirit of the living
        creature was in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the glory of the Lord  departed from the threshold of the temple
        and stood over the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the cherubim lifted their wings and mounted up from the earth
        in my sight. When they went out, the wheels were beside them; and they stood
        at the door of the east gate of the Lord\u2019s house, and the glory of the
        God of Israel was above them."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is the living creature I saw under the God of Israel by the
        River Chebar, and I knew they were cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Each one had four faces and each one four wings, and the likeness
        of the hands of a man was under their wings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And the likeness of their faces was the same as the faces which I
        had seen by the River Chebar, their appearance and their persons. They each
        went straight forward.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Wicked Counselors'
      title: Judgment on Wicked Counselors
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Spirit lifted me up and brought me to the East Gate of the
        Lord\u2019s house, which faces eastward; and there at the door of the gate
        were twenty-five men, among whom I saw Jaazaniah the son of Azzur, and Pelatiah
        the son of Benaiah, princes of the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And He said to me: \u201CSon of man, these are the men who devise
        iniquity and give wicked counsel in this city, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "who say, \u2018The  time  is not near to build houses; this city 
        is the caldron, and we are the meat.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore prophesy against them, prophesy, O son of man!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Spirit of the Lord fell upon me, and said to me, \u201CSpeak!
        \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CThus you have said, O house of Israel; for
        I know the things that come into your mind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You have multiplied your slain in this city, and you have filled
        its streets with the slain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CYour slain whom you have
        laid in its midst, they are the meat, and this city  is the caldron; but
        I shall bring you out of the midst of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You have feared the sword; and I will bring a sword upon you,\u201D
        says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd I will bring you out of its midst, and deliver you into
        the hands of strangers, and execute judgments on you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall fall by the sword. I will judge you at the border of Israel.
        Then you shall know that I am the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This city shall not be your caldron, nor shall you be the meat in
        its midst. I will judge you at the border of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And you shall know that I am the Lord; for you have not walked in
        My statutes nor executed My judgments, but have done according to the customs
        of the Gentiles which are all around you.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: God Will Restore Israel'
      title: God Will Restore Israel
      number: 13
      content: "Now it happened, while I was prophesying, that Pelatiah the son of
        Benaiah died. Then I fell on my face and cried with a loud voice, and said,
        \u201CAh, Lord God! Will You make a complete end of the remnant of Israel?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSon of man, your brethren, your relatives, your countrymen,
        and all the house of Israel in its entirety, are those about whom the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem have said, \u2018Get far away from the Lord; this land has been
        given to us as a possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CAlthough I have
        cast them far off among the Gentiles, and although I have scattered them
        among the countries, yet I shall be a little sanctuary for them in the countries
        where they have gone.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will gather
        you from the peoples, assemble you from the countries where you have been
        scattered, and I will give you the land of Israel.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they will go there, and they will take away all its detestable
        things and all its abominations from there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then I will give them one heart, and I will put a new spirit within
        them, and take the stony heart out of their flesh, and give them a heart
        of flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that they may walk in My statutes and keep My judgments and do them;
        and they shall be My people, and I will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But as  for  those whose hearts follow the desire for their detestable
        things and their abominations, I will recompense their deeds on their own
        heads,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the cherubim lifted up their wings, with the wheels beside them,
        and the glory of the God of Israel was high above them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And the glory of the Lord went up from the midst of the city and stood
        on the mountain, which is on the east side of the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the Spirit took me up and brought me in a vision by the Spirit
        of God into Chaldea, to those in captivity. And the vision that I had seen
        went up from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So I spoke to those in captivity of all the things the Lord had shown
        me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Captivity Portrayed"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Captivity Portrayed"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, you dwell in the midst of a rebellious house, which
        has eyes to see but does not see, and ears to hear but does not hear; for
        they are a rebellious house."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CTherefore, son of man, prepare your belongings for captivity,
        and go into captivity by day in their sight. You shall go from your place
        into captivity to another place in their sight. It may be that they will
        consider, though they are a rebellious house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'By day you shall bring out your belongings in their sight, as though
        going into captivity; and at evening you shall go in their sight, like those
        who go into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Dig through the wall in their sight, and carry your  belongings out
        through it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In their sight you shall bear them on your shoulders and carry them
        out at twilight; you shall cover your face, so that you cannot see the ground,
        for I have made you a sign to the house of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: So I did as I was commanded. I brought out my belongings by day, as
        though going into captivity, and at evening I dug through the wall with my
        hand. I brought them out at twilight, and I bore them on my shoulder in their
        sight.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And in the morning the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSon of man, has not the house of Israel, the rebellious house,
        said to you, \u2018What are you doing?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CThis burden concerns
        the prince in Jerusalem and all the house of Israel who are among them.\u201D
        \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Say, \u2018I am a sign to you. As I have done, so shall it be done
        to them; they shall be carried away into captivity.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the prince who is among them shall bear his  belongings on his
        shoulder at twilight and go out. They shall dig through the wall to carry
        them out through it. He shall cover his face, so that he cannot see the ground
        with his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will also spread My net over him, and he shall be caught in My
        snare. I will bring him to Babylon, to the land of the Chaldeans; yet he
        shall not see it, though he shall die there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I will scatter to every wind all who are around him to help him, and
        all his troops; and I will draw out the sword after them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThen they shall know that I am the Lord, when I scatter them
        among the nations and disperse them throughout the countries. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Judgment Not Postponed'
      title: Judgment Not Postponed
      number: 16
      content: "But I will spare a few of their men from the sword, from famine,
        and from pestilence, that they may declare all their abominations among the
        Gentiles wherever they go. Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CSon of man, eat your bread with quaking, and drink your water
        with trembling and anxiety. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And say to the people of the land, \u2018Thus says the Lord God to
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the land of Israel: \u201CThey shall
        eat their bread with anxiety, and drink their water with dread, so that her
        land may be emptied of all who are in it, because of the violence of all
        those who dwell in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the cities that are inhabited shall be laid waste, and the land
        shall become desolate; and you shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CSon of man, what is this proverb that you people have about
        the land of Israel, which says, \u2018The days are prolonged, and every vision
        fails\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Tell them therefore, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will lay
        this proverb to rest, and they shall no more use it as a proverb in Israel.\u201D
        \u2019 But say to them, \u2018 \u201CThe days are at hand, and the fulfillment
        of every vision. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For no more shall there be any false vision or flattering divination
        within the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I am the Lord. I speak, and the word which I speak will come
        to pass; it will no more be postponed; for in your days, O rebellious house,
        I will say the word and perform it,\u201D says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CSon of man, look, the house of Israel is saying, \u2018The
        vision that he sees is  for many days from  now, and he prophesies of times
        far off.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CNone of
        My words will be postponed any more, but the word which I speak will be done,\u201D
        says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Foolish Prophets'
      title: Woe to Foolish Prophets
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel who prophesy,
        and say to those who prophesy out of their own heart, \u2018Hear the word
        of the Lord!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CWoe to the foolish prophets, who follow
        their own spirit and have seen nothing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'O Israel, your prophets are like foxes in the deserts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have not gone up into the gaps to build a wall for the house
        of Israel to stand in battle on the day of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They have envisioned futility and false divination, saying, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord!\u2019 But the Lord has not sent them; yet they hope that the
        word may be confirmed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Have you not seen a futile vision, and have you not spoken false
        divination? You say, \u2018The Lord says,\u2019 but I have not spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause you have spoken nonsense
        and envisioned lies, therefore I am indeed against you,\u201D says the Lord
        God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy hand will be against the prophets who envision futility
        and who divine lies; they shall not be in the assembly of My people, nor
        be written in the record of the house of Israel, nor shall they enter into
        the land of Israel. Then you shall know that I am the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CBecause, indeed, because they have seduced My people, saying,
        \u2018Peace!\u2019 when there  is no peace\u2014and one builds a wall, and
        they plaster it with untempered mortar\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'say to those who plaster it with untempered mortar, that it will
        fall. There will be flooding rain, and you, O great hailstones, shall fall;
        and a stormy wind shall tear it down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Surely, when the wall has fallen, will it not be said to you, \u2018Where
        is the mortar with which you plastered it?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will cause a stormy wind
        to break forth in My fury; and there shall be a flooding rain in My anger,
        and great hailstones in fury to consume it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So I will break down the wall you have plastered with untempered mortar,
        and bring it down to the ground, so that its foundation will be uncovered;
        it will fall, and you shall be consumed in the midst of it. Then you shall
        know that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus will I accomplish My wrath on the wall and on those who
        have plastered it with untempered mortar; and I will say to you, \u2018The
        wall is no more, nor those who plastered it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "that  is, the prophets of Israel who prophesy concerning Jerusalem,
        and who see visions of peace for her when there  is no peace,\u2019 \u201D
        says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CLikewise, son of man, set your face against the daughters of
        your people, who prophesy out of their own heart; prophesy against them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CWoe to the women who
        sew magic charms on their sleeves and make veils for the heads of people
        of every height to hunt souls! Will you hunt the souls of My people, and
        keep yourselves alive? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And will you profane Me among My people for handfuls of barley and
        for pieces of bread, killing people who should not die, and keeping people
        alive who should not live, by your lying to My people who listen to lies?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CBehold, I am against
        your magic charms by which you hunt souls there like birds. I will tear them
        from your arms, and let the souls go, the souls you hunt like birds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will also tear off your veils and deliver My people out of your
        hand, and they shall no longer be as prey in your hand. Then you shall know
        that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CBecause with lies you have made the heart of the righteous
        sad, whom I have not made sad; and you have strengthened the hands of the
        wicked, so that he does not turn from his wicked way to save his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Therefore you shall no longer envision futility nor practice divination;
        for I will deliver My people out of your hand, and you shall know that I
        am the Lord.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idolatry Will Be Punished'
      title: Idolatry Will Be Punished
      number: 1
      content: 'Now some of the elders of Israel came to me and sat before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CSon of man, these men have set up their idols in their hearts,
        and put before them that which causes them to stumble into iniquity. Should
        I let Myself be inquired of at all by them?"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTherefore speak to them, and say to them, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord God: \u201CEveryone of the house of Israel who sets up his idols in
        his heart, and puts before him what causes him to stumble into iniquity,
        and then comes to the prophet, I the Lord will answer him who comes, according
        to the multitude of his idols, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "that I may seize the house of Israel by their heart, because they
        are all estranged from Me by their idols.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CTherefore say to the house of Israel, \u2018Thus says the Lord
        God: \u201CRepent, turn away from your idols, and turn your faces away from
        all your abominations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For anyone of the house of Israel, or of the strangers who dwell
        in Israel, who separates himself from Me and sets up his idols in his heart
        and puts before him what causes him to stumble into iniquity, then comes
        to a prophet to inquire of him concerning Me, I the Lord will answer him
        by Myself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I will set My face against that man and make him a sign and a proverb,
        and I will cut him off from the midst of My people. Then you shall know that
        I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd if the prophet is induced to speak anything, I the Lord 
        have induced that prophet, and I will stretch out My hand against him and
        destroy him from among My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they shall bear their iniquity; the punishment of the prophet
        shall be the same as the punishment of the one who inquired, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Judgment on Persistent Unfaithfulness'
      title: Judgment on Persistent Unfaithfulness
      number: 11
      content: "that the house of Israel may no longer stray from Me, nor be profaned
        anymore with all their transgressions, but that they may be My people and
        I may be their God,\u201C says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The word of the Lord came again to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CSon of man, when a land sins against Me by persistent unfaithfulness,
        I will stretch out My hand against it; I will cut off its supply of bread,
        send famine on it, and cut off man and beast from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Even if these three men, Noah, Daniel, and Job, were in it, they
        would deliver only themselves by their righteousness,\u201D says the Lord
        God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf I cause wild beasts to pass through the land, and they empty
        it, and make it so desolate that no man may pass through because of the beasts, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "even  though these three men were in it, as I live,\u201D says the
        Lord God, \u201Cthey would deliver neither sons nor daughters; only they
        would be delivered, and the land would be desolate."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201COr if  I bring a sword on that land, and say, \u2018Sword,
        go through the land,\u2019 and I cut off man and beast from it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "even though these three men were in it, as I live,\u201D says the
        Lord God, \u201Cthey would deliver neither sons nor daughters, but only they
        themselves would be delivered."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201COr if I send a pestilence into that land and pour out My fury
        on it in blood, and cut off from it man and beast, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "even though Noah, Daniel, and Job were in it, as I live,\u201D says
        the Lord God, \u201Cthey would deliver neither son nor daughter; they would
        deliver only themselves by their righteousness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For thus says the Lord God: \u201CHow much more it shall be when
        I send My four severe judgments on Jerusalem\u2014the sword and famine and
        wild beasts and pestilence\u2014to cut off man and beast from it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet behold, there shall be left in it a remnant who will be brought
        out, both sons and daughters; surely they will come out to you, and you will
        see their ways and their doings. Then you will be comforted concerning the
        disaster that I have brought upon Jerusalem, all that I have brought upon
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they will comfort you, when you see their ways and their doings;
        and you shall know that I have done nothing without cause that I have done
        in it,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Outcast Vine'
      title: The Outcast Vine
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, how is the wood of the vine better than any other
        wood, the vine branch which is among the trees of the forest? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is wood taken from it to make any object? Or can men make a peg from
        it to hang any vessel on? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Instead, it is thrown into the fire for fuel; the fire devours both
        ends of it, and its middle is burned. Is it useful for any work? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Indeed, when it was whole, no object could be made from it. How much
        less will it be useful for any work when the fire has devoured it, and it
        is burned?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Like the wood of the
        vine among the trees of the forest, which I have given to the fire for fuel,
        so I will give up the inhabitants of Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and I will set My face against them. They will go out from one fire,
        but another fire shall devour them. Then you shall know that I am the Lord,
        when I set My face against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus I will make the land desolate, because they have persisted in
        unfaithfulness,\u2019 says the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Love for Jerusalem"
      title: "God\u2019s Love for Jerusalem"
      number: 1
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, cause Jerusalem to know her abominations, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God to Jerusalem: \u201CYour birth
        and your nativity are from the land of Canaan; your father was an Amorite
        and your mother a Hittite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As  for your nativity, on the day you were born your navel cord was
        not cut, nor were you washed in water to cleanse you; you were not rubbed
        with salt nor wrapped in swaddling cloths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: No eye pitied you, to do any of these things for you, to have compassion
        on you; but you were thrown out into the open field, when you yourself were
        loathed on the day you were born.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd when I passed by you and saw you struggling in your own
        blood, I said to you in your blood, \u2018Live!\u2019 Yes, I said to you
        in your blood, \u2018Live!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I made you thrive like a plant in the field; and you grew, matured,
        and became very beautiful. Your breasts were formed, your hair grew, but
        you were naked and bare.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen I passed by you again and looked upon you, indeed your
        time was the time of love; so I spread My wing over you and covered your
        nakedness. Yes, I swore an oath to you and entered into a covenant with you,
        and you became Mine,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThen I washed you in water; yes, I thoroughly washed off your
        blood, and I anointed you with oil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I clothed you in embroidered cloth and gave you sandals of badger
        skin; I clothed you with fine linen and covered you with silk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I adorned you with ornaments, put bracelets on your wrists, and a
        chain on your neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I put a jewel in your nose, earrings in your ears, and a beautiful
        crown on your head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Thus you were adorned with gold and silver, and your clothing was 
        of fine linen, silk, and embroidered cloth. You ate pastry  of fine flour,
        honey, and oil. You were exceedingly beautiful, and succeeded to royalty. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Jerusalem\u2019s Harlotry"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Harlotry"
      number: 14
      content: "Your fame went out among the nations because of your beauty, for
        it was perfect through My splendor which I had bestowed on you,\u201D says
        the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut you trusted in your own beauty, played the harlot because
        of your fame, and poured out your harlotry on everyone passing by who would 
        have it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You took some of your garments and adorned multicolored high places
        for yourself, and played the harlot on them. Such things should not happen,
        nor be. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You have also taken your beautiful jewelry from My gold and My silver,
        which I had given you, and made for yourself male images and played the harlot
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You took your embroidered garments and covered them, and you set
        My oil and My incense before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Also My food which I gave you\u2014the pastry of fine flour, oil,
        and honey which I fed you\u2014you set it before them as sweet incense; and
        so it was,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CMoreover you took your sons and your daughters, whom you bore
        to Me, and these you sacrificed to them to be devoured. Were your acts of
        harlotry a small matter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that you have slain My children and offered them up to them by causing
        them to pass through the  fire? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And in all your abominations and acts of harlotry you did not remember
        the days of your youth, when you were naked and bare, struggling in your
        blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThen it was so, after all your wickedness\u2014\u2018Woe, woe
        to you!\u2019 says the Lord God\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'that  you also built for yourself a shrine, and made a high place
        for yourself in every street. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You built your high places at the head of every road, and made your
        beauty to be abhorred. You offered yourself to everyone who passed by, and
        multiplied your acts of harlotry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: You also committed harlotry with the Egyptians, your very fleshly
        neighbors, and increased your acts of harlotry to provoke Me to anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, therefore, I stretched out My hand against you, diminished
        your allotment, and gave you up to the will of those who hate you, the daughters
        of the Philistines, who were ashamed of your lewd behavior. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You also played the harlot with the Assyrians, because you were insatiable;
        indeed you played the harlot with them and still were not satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Moreover you multiplied your acts of harlotry as far as the land of
        the trader, Chaldea; and even then you were not satisfied.
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jerusalem\u2019s Adultery"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Adultery"
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CHow degenerate is your heart!\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cseeing
        you do all these things, the deeds of a brazen harlot."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou erected your shrine at the head of every road, and built
        your high place in every street. Yet you were not like a harlot, because
        you scorned payment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You  are an adulterous wife, who takes strangers instead of her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Men make payment to all harlots, but you made your payments to all
        your lovers, and hired them to come to you from all around for your harlotry. '
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Jerusalem\u2019s Lovers Will Abuse Her"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Lovers Will Abuse Her"
      number: 34
      content: "You are the opposite of other women in your harlotry, because no
        one solicited you to be a harlot. In that you gave payment but no payment
        was given you, therefore you are the opposite.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Now then, O harlot, hear the word of the Lord! "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause your filthiness was poured
        out and your nakedness uncovered in your harlotry with your lovers, and with
        all your abominable idols, and because of the blood of your children which
        you gave to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'surely, therefore, I will gather all your lovers with whom you took
        pleasure, all those you loved, and all those you hated; I will gather them
        from all around against you and will uncover your nakedness to them, that
        they may see all your nakedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And I will judge you as women who break wedlock or shed blood are
        judged; I will bring blood upon you in fury and jealousy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: I will also give you into their hand, and they shall throw down your
        shrines and break down your high places. They shall also strip you of your
        clothes, take your beautiful jewelry, and leave you naked and bare.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CThey shall also bring up an assembly against you, and they
        shall stone you with stones and thrust you through with their swords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'They shall burn your houses with fire, and execute judgments on you
        in the sight of many women; and I will make you cease playing the harlot,
        and you shall no longer hire lovers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So I will lay to rest My fury toward you, and My jealousy shall depart
        from you. I will be quiet, and be angry no more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: More Wicked than Samaria and Sodom'
      title: More Wicked than Samaria and Sodom
      number: 43
      content: "Because you did not remember the days of your youth, but agitated
        Me with all these things, surely I will also recompense your deeds on your 
        own head,\u201D says the Lord God. \u201CAnd you shall not commit lewdness
        in addition to all your abominations."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CIndeed everyone who quotes proverbs will use this proverb against
        you: \u2018Like mother, like daughter!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "You are your mother\u2019s daughter, loathing husband and children;
        and you are the sister of your sisters, who loathed their husbands and children;
        your mother was a Hittite and your father an Amorite."
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CYour elder sister is Samaria, who dwells with her daughters
        to the north of you; and your younger sister, who dwells to the south of
        you, is Sodom and her daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: You did not walk in their ways nor act according to their abominations;
        but, as if  that  were too little, you became more corrupt than they in all
        your ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cneither your sister
        Sodom nor her daughters have done as you and your daughters have done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Look, this was the iniquity of your sister Sodom: She and her daughter
        had pride, fullness of food, and abundance of idleness; neither did she strengthen
        the hand of the poor and needy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: And they were haughty and committed abomination before Me; therefore
        I took them away as I saw fit.
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CSamaria did not commit half of your sins; but you have multiplied
        your abominations more than they, and have justified your sisters by all
        the abominations which you have done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: You who judged your sisters, bear your own shame also, because the
        sins which you committed were more abominable than theirs; they are more
        righteous than you. Yes, be disgraced also, and bear your own shame, because
        you justified your sisters.
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "\u201CWhen I bring back their captives, the captives of Sodom and
        her daughters, and the captives of Samaria and her daughters, then I  will 
        also  bring  back  the captives of your captivity among them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'that you may bear your own shame and be disgraced by all that you
        did when you comforted them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'When your sisters, Sodom and her daughters, return to their former
        state, and Samaria and her daughters return to their former state, then you
        and your daughters will return to your former state. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'For your sister Sodom was not a byword in your mouth in the days
        of your pride, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'before your wickedness was uncovered. It was like the time of the
        reproach of the daughters of Syria and all those around her, and of the daughters
        of the Philistines, who despise you everywhere. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "You have paid for your lewdness and your abominations,\u201D says
        the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: An Everlasting Covenant'
      title: An Everlasting Covenant
      number: 59
      content: "For thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will deal with you as you have
        done, who despised the oath by breaking the covenant."
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "\u201CNevertheless I will remember My covenant with you in the days
        of your youth, and I will establish an everlasting covenant with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Then you will remember your ways and be ashamed, when you receive
        your older and your younger sisters; for I will give them to you for daughters,
        but not because of My covenant with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'And I will establish My covenant with you. Then you shall know that
        I am the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "that you may remember and be ashamed, and never open your mouth anymore
        because of your shame, when I provide you an atonement for all you have done,\u201D
        says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Eagles and the Vine'
      title: The Eagles and the Vine
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, pose a riddle, and speak a parable to the house
        of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CA great eagle with large
        wings and long pinions,Full of feathers of various colors,Came to LebanonAnd
        took from the cedar the highest branch."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He cropped off its topmost young twigAnd carried it to a land of trade;He
        set it in a city of merchants.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then he took some of the seed of the landAnd planted it in a fertile
        field;He placed it by abundant watersAnd set it like a willow tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And it grew and became a spreading vine of low stature;Its branches
        turned toward him,But its roots were under it.So it became a vine,Brought
        forth branches,And put forth shoots.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut there was another great eagle with large wings and many
        feathers;And behold, this vine bent its roots toward him,And stretched its
        branches toward him,From the garden terrace where it had been planted,That
        he might water it."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It was planted in good soil by many waters,To bring forth branches,
        bear fruit,And become a majestic vine.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSay, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CWill it thrive?Will
        he not pull up its roots,Cut off its fruit,And leave it to wither?All of
        its spring leaves will wither,And no great power or many peopleWill be needed
        to pluck it up by its roots."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Behold, it  is planted,Will it thrive?Will it not utterly wither
        when the east wind touches it?It will wither in the garden terrace where
        it grew.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSay now to the rebellious house: \u2018Do you not know what
        these things  mean?\u2019 Tell them, \u2018Indeed the king of Babylon went
        to Jerusalem and took its king and princes, and led them with him to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he took the king\u2019s offspring, made a covenant with him,
        and put him under oath. He also took away the mighty of the land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'that the kingdom might be brought low and not lift itself up, but
        that by keeping his covenant it might stand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But he rebelled against him by sending his ambassadors to Egypt, that
        they might give him horses and many people. Will he prosper? Will he who
        does such things escape? Can he break a covenant and still be delivered?
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018As I live,\u2019 says the Lord God, \u2018surely in the place
        where the king dwells who made him king, whose oath he despised and whose
        covenant he broke\u2014with him in the midst of Babylon he shall die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Nor will Pharaoh with his mighty army and great company do anything
        in the war, when they heap up a siege mound and build a wall to cut off many
        persons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Since he despised the oath by breaking the covenant, and in fact
        gave his hand and still did all these things, he shall not escape.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CAs I live, surely My oath
        which he despised, and My covenant which he broke, I will recompense on his
        own head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will spread My net over him, and he shall be taken in My snare.
        I will bring him to Babylon and try him there for the treason which he committed
        against Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Israel Exalted at Last'
      title: Israel Exalted at Last
      number: 21
      content: "All his fugitives with all his troops shall fall by the sword, and
        those who remain shall be scattered to every wind; and you shall know that
        I, the Lord, have spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will take also one of the highest
        branches of the high cedar and set it out. I will crop off from the topmost
        of its young twigs a tender one, and will plant it on a high and prominent
        mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'On the mountain height of Israel I will plant it; and it will bring
        forth boughs, and bear fruit, and be a majestic cedar. Under it will dwell
        birds of every sort; in the shadow of its branches they will dwell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And all the trees of the field shall know that I, the Lord, have
        brought down the high tree and exalted the low tree, dried up the green tree
        and made the dry tree flourish; I, the Lord, have spoken and have done it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A False Proverb Refuted'
      title: A False Proverb Refuted
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me again, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhat do you mean when you use this proverb concerning the land
        of Israel, saying:\u2018The fathers have eaten sour grapes,And the children\u2019s
        teeth are set on edge\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cyou shall no longer
        use this proverb in Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBehold, all souls are Mine;The soul of the fatherAs well as
        the soul of the son is Mine;The soul who sins shall die."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But if a man is justAnd does what is lawful and right;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If he has not eaten on the mountains,Nor lifted up his eyes to the
        idols of the house of Israel,Nor defiled his neighbor\u2019s wife,Nor approached
        a woman during her impurity;"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: If he has not oppressed anyone,But has restored to the debtor his
        pledge;Has robbed no one by violence,But has given his bread to the hungryAnd
        covered the naked with clothing;
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: If he has not exacted usuryNor taken any increase,But has withdrawn
        his hand from iniquityAnd  executed true judgment between man and man;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If he has walked in My statutesAnd kept My judgments faithfully\u2014He
        is just;He shall surely live!\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf he begets a son who  is a robberOr a shedder of blood,Who
        does any of these things"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And does none of those duties,But has eaten on the mountainsOr defiled
        his neighbor\u2019s wife;"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: If he has oppressed the poor and needy,Robbed by violence,Not restored
        the pledge,Lifted his eyes to the idols,Or  committed abomination;
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If he has exacted usuryOr taken increase\u2014Shall he then live?He
        shall not live!If he has done any of these abominations,He shall surely die;His
        blood shall be upon him."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIf, however, he begets a sonWho sees all the sins which his
        father has done,And considers but does not do likewise;"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Who has not eaten on the mountains,Nor lifted his eyes to the idols
        of the house of Israel,Nor defiled his neighbor\u2019s wife;"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Has not oppressed anyone,Nor withheld a pledge,Nor robbed by violence,But
        has given his bread to the hungryAnd covered the naked with clothing;
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Who has withdrawn his hand from the poorAnd not received usury or
        increase,But has executed My judgmentsAnd walked in My statutes\u2014He shall
        not die for the iniquity of his father;He shall surely live!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Turn and Live'
      title: Turn and Live
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAs  for his father,Because he cruelly oppressed,Robbed his
        brother by violence,And did what is not good among his people,Behold, he
        shall die for his iniquity."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYet you say, \u2018Why should the son not bear the guilt of
        the father?\u2019 Because the son has done what is lawful and right, and
        has kept all My statutes and observed them, he shall surely live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The soul who sins shall die. The son shall not bear the guilt of the
        father, nor the father bear the guilt of the son. The righteousness of the
        righteous shall be upon himself, and the wickedness of the wicked shall be
        upon himself.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CBut if a wicked man turns from all his sins which he has committed,
        keeps all My statutes, and does what is lawful and right, he shall surely
        live; he shall not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'None of the transgressions which he has committed shall be remembered
        against him; because of the righteousness which he has done, he shall live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Do I have any pleasure at all that the wicked should die?\u201D says
        the Lord God, \u201Cand not that he should turn from his ways and live?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CBut when a righteous man turns away from his righteousness
        and commits iniquity, and does according to all the abominations that the
        wicked man does, shall he live? All the righteousness which he has done shall
        not be remembered; because of the unfaithfulness of which he is guilty and
        the sin which he has committed, because of them he shall die."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYet you say, \u2018The way of the Lord is not fair.\u2019 Hear
        now, O house of Israel, is it not My way which is fair, and your ways which
        are not fair? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When a righteous man turns away from his righteousness, commits iniquity,
        and dies in it, it is because of the iniquity which he has done that he dies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Again, when a wicked man turns away from the wickedness which he
        committed, and does what is lawful and right, he preserves himself alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Because he considers and turns away from all the transgressions which
        he committed, he shall surely live; he shall not die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Yet the house of Israel says, \u2018The way of the Lord is not fair.\u2019
        O house of Israel, is it not My ways which are fair, and your ways which
        are not fair?"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will judge you, O house of Israel, every one according
        to his ways,\u201D says the Lord God. \u201CRepent, and turn from all your
        transgressions, so that iniquity will not be your ruin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Cast away from you all the transgressions which you have committed,
        and get yourselves a new heart and a new spirit. For why should you die,
        O house of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For I have no pleasure in the death of one who dies,\u201D says the
        Lord God. \u201CTherefore turn and live!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Degraded'
      title: Israel Degraded
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMoreover take up a lamentation for the princes of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and say:\u2018What is your mother? A lioness:She lay down among the
        lions;Among the young lions she nourished her cubs."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: She brought up one of her cubs,And he became a young lion;He learned
        to catch prey,And he devoured men.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The nations also heard of him;He was trapped in their pit,And they
        brought him with chains to the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018When she saw that she waited, that her hope was lost,She took
        another of her cubs and made him a young lion."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He roved among the lions,And became a young lion;He learned to catch
        prey;He devoured men.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He knew their desolate places,And laid waste their cities;The land
        with its fullness was desolatedBy the noise of his roaring.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then the nations set against him from the provinces on every side,And
        spread their net over him;He was trapped in their pit.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They put him in a cage with chains,And brought him to the king of
        Babylon;They brought him in nets,That his voice should no longer be heard
        on the mountains of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Your mother was  like a vine in your bloodline,Planted by the
        waters,Fruitful and full of branchesBecause of many waters."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: She had strong branches for scepters of rulers.She towered in stature
        above the thick branches,And was seen in her height amid the dense foliage.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But she was plucked up in fury,She was cast down to the ground,And
        the east wind dried her fruit.Her strong branches were broken and withered;The
        fire consumed them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And now she is planted in the wilderness,In a dry and thirsty land.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Fire has come out from a rod of her branchesAnd devoured her fruit,So
        that she has no strong branch\u2014 a scepter for ruling.\u2019 \u201DThis
        is a lamentation, and has become a lamentation."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rebellions of Israel'
      title: The Rebellions of Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'It came to pass in the seventh year, in the fifth month, on the tenth
        day of the month, that  certain of the elders of Israel came to inquire of
        the Lord, and sat before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CSon of man, speak to the elders of Israel, and say to them,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CHave you come to inquire of Me? As I
        live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201CI will not be inquired of by you.\u201D
        \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Will you judge them, son of man, will you judge them? Then make known
        to them the abominations of their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSay to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201COn the day
        when I chose Israel and raised My hand in an oath to the descendants of the
        house of Jacob, and made Myself known to them in the land of Egypt, I raised
        My hand in an oath to them, saying, \u2018I am the Lord your God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "On that day I raised My hand in an oath to them, to bring them out
        of the land of Egypt into a land that I had searched out for them, \u2018flowing
        with milk and honey,\u2019 the glory of all lands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said to them, \u2018Each of you, throw away the abominations
        which are before his eyes, and do not defile yourselves with the idols of
        Egypt. I am the Lord your God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they rebelled against Me and would not obey Me. They did not
        all cast away the abominations which were before their eyes, nor did they
        forsake the idols of Egypt. Then I said, \u2018I will pour out My fury on
        them and fulfill My anger against them in the midst of the land of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But I acted for My name\u2019s sake, that it should not be profaned
        before the Gentiles among whom they were, in whose sight I had made Myself
        known to them, to bring them out of the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore I made them go out of the land of Egypt and brought
        them into the wilderness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And I gave them My statutes and showed them My judgments, \u2018which,
        if a man does, he shall live by them.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Moreover I also gave them My Sabbaths, to be a sign between them
        and Me, that they might know that I am the Lord who sanctifies them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet the house of Israel rebelled against Me in the wilderness; they
        did not walk in My statutes; they despised My judgments, \u2018which, if
        a man does, he shall live by them\u2019; and they greatly defiled My Sabbaths.
        Then I said I would pour out My fury on them in the wilderness, to consume
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But I acted for My name\u2019s sake, that it should not be profaned
        before the Gentiles, in whose sight I had brought them out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So I also raised My hand in an oath to them in the wilderness, that
        I would not bring them into the land which I had given them,  \u2018flowing
        with milk and honey,\u2019 the glory of all lands, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'because they despised My judgments and did not walk in My statutes,
        but profaned My Sabbaths; for their heart went after their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Nevertheless My eye spared them from destruction. I did not make an
        end of them in the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut I said to their children in the wilderness, \u2018Do not
        walk in the statutes of your fathers, nor observe their judgments, nor defile
        yourselves with their idols. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I am the Lord your God: Walk in My statutes, keep My judgments, and
        do them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "hallow My Sabbaths, and they will be a sign between Me and you, that
        you may know that I am the Lord your God.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNotwithstanding, the children rebelled against Me; they did
        not walk in My statutes, and were not careful to observe My judgments, \u2018which,
        if a man does, he shall live by them\u2019; but they profaned My Sabbaths.
        Then I said I would pour out My fury on them and fulfill My anger against
        them in the wilderness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Nevertheless I withdrew My hand and acted for My name\u2019s sake,
        that it should not be profaned in the sight of the Gentiles, in whose sight
        I had brought them out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Also I raised My hand in an oath to those in the wilderness, that
        I would scatter them among the Gentiles and disperse them throughout the
        countries, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "because they had not executed My judgments, but had despised My statutes,
        profaned My Sabbaths, and their eyes were fixed on their fathers\u2019 idols."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTherefore I also gave them up to statutes that  were not good,
        and judgments by which they could not live; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and I pronounced them unclean because of their ritual gifts, in that
        they caused all their firstborn to pass through the  fire, that I might make
        them desolate and that they might know that I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CTherefore, son of man, speak to the house of Israel, and say
        to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CIn this too your fathers have
        blasphemed Me, by being unfaithful to Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When I brought them into the land concerning which I had raised My
        hand in an oath to give them, and they saw all the high hills and all the
        thick trees, there they offered their sacrifices and provoked Me with their
        offerings. There they also sent up their sweet aroma and poured out their
        drink offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then I said to them, \u2018What is this high place to which you go?\u2019
        So its name is called Bamah to this day.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore say to the house of Israel, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:
        \u201CAre you defiling yourselves in the manner of your fathers, and committing
        harlotry according to their abominations? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For when you offer your gifts and make your sons pass through the
        fire, you defile yourselves with all your idols, even to this day. So shall
        I be inquired of by you, O house of Israel? As I live,\u201D says the Lord
        God, \u201CI will not be inquired of by you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: God Will Restore Israel'
      title: God Will Restore Israel
      number: 32
      content: "What you have in your mind shall never be, when you say, \u2018We
        will be like the Gentiles, like the families in other countries, serving
        wood and stone.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Csurely with a mighty
        hand, with an outstretched arm, and with fury poured out, I will rule over
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'I will bring you out from the peoples and gather you out of the countries
        where you are scattered, with a mighty hand, with an outstretched arm, and
        with fury poured out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And I will bring you into the wilderness of the peoples, and there
        I will plead My case with you face to face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Just as I pleaded My case with your fathers in the wilderness of
        the land of Egypt, so I will plead My case with you,\u201D says the Lord
        God."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CI will make you pass under the rod, and I will bring you into
        the bond of the covenant; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: I will purge the rebels from among you, and those who transgress against
        Me; I will bring them out of the country where they dwell, but they shall
        not enter the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CAs for you, O house of Israel,\u201D thus says the Lord God:
        \u201CGo, serve every one of you his idols\u2014and hereafter\u2014if you
        will not obey Me; but profane My holy name no more with your gifts and your
        idols. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For on My holy mountain, on the mountain height of Israel,\u201D
        says the Lord God, \u201Cthere all the house of Israel, all of them in the
        land, shall serve Me; there I will accept them, and there I will require
        your offerings and the firstfruits of your sacrifices, together with all
        your holy things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'I will accept you as a sweet aroma when I bring you out from the
        peoples and gather you out of the countries where you have been scattered;
        and I will be hallowed in you before the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then you shall know that I am the Lord, when I bring you into the
        land of Israel, into the country for which I raised My hand in an oath to
        give to your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And there you shall remember your ways and all your doings with which
        you were defiled; and you shall loathe yourselves in your own sight because
        of all the evils that you have committed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: Fire in the Forest'
      title: Fire in the Forest
      number: 44
      content: "Then you shall know that I am the Lord, when I have dealt with you
        for My name\u2019s sake, not according to your wicked ways nor according
        to your corrupt doings, O house of Israel,\u201D says the Lord God.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Furthermore the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face toward the south; preach against
        the south and prophesy against the forest land, the South, "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "and say to the forest of the South, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord!
        Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBehold, I will kindle a fire in you, and it
        shall devour every green tree and every dry tree in you; the blazing flame
        shall not be quenched, and all faces from the south to the north shall be
        scorched by it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "All flesh shall see that I, the Lord, have kindled it; it shall not
        be quenched.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord God! They say of me, \u2018Does he not
        speak parables?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Babylon, the Sword of God'
      title: Babylon, the Sword of God
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face toward Jerusalem, preach against
        the holy places, and prophesy against the land of Israel; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say to the land of Israel, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold,
        I am  against you, and I will draw My sword out of its sheath and cut off
        both righteous and wicked from you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because I will cut off both righteous and wicked from you, therefore
        My sword shall go out of its sheath against all flesh from south to north, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "that all flesh may know that I, the Lord, have drawn My sword out
        of its sheath; it shall not return anymore.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sigh therefore, son of man, with a breaking heart, and sigh with
        bitterness before their eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And it shall be when they say to you, \u2018Why are you sighing?\u2019
        that you shall answer, \u2018Because of the news; when it comes, every heart
        will melt, all hands will be feeble, every spirit will faint, and all knees
        will be weak as water. Behold, it is coming and shall be brought to pass,\u2019
        says the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSon of man, prophesy and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord!\u2019
        Say:\u2018A sword, a sword is sharpenedAnd also polished!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Sharpened to make a dreadful slaughter,Polished to flash like lightning!Should
        we then make mirth?It despises the scepter of My son,As  it  does all wood.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And He has given it to be polished,That it may be handled;This sword
        is sharpened, and it is polishedTo be given into the hand of the slayer.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CCry and wail, son of man;For it will be against My people,Against
        all the princes of Israel.Terrors including the sword will be against My
        people;Therefore strike your thigh."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBecause it  is  a testing,And what if the  sword despises even
        the scepter?The  scepter shall be no more,\u201Dsays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou therefore, son of man, prophesy,And strike your hands together.The
        third time let the sword do double damage.It is the sword that slays,The
        sword that slays the great men,That enters their private chambers."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I have set the point of the sword against all their gates,That the
        heart may melt and many may stumble.Ah! It  is made bright;It  is grasped
        for slaughter:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSwords at the ready!Thrust right!Set your blade!Thrust left\u2014Wherever
        your edge is ordered!"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI also will beat My fists together,And I will cause My fury
        to rest;I, the Lord, have spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me again, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAnd son of man, appoint for yourself two ways for the sword
        of the king of Babylon to go; both of them shall go from the same land. Make
        a sign; put it at the head of the road to the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Appoint a road for the sword to go to Rabbah of the Ammonites, and
        to Judah, into fortified Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the king of Babylon stands at the parting of the road, at the
        fork of the two roads, to use divination: he shakes the arrows, he consults
        the images, he looks at the liver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In his right hand is the divination for Jerusalem: to set up battering
        rams, to call for a slaughter, to lift the voice with shouting, to set battering
        rams against the gates, to heap up a siege mound, and to build a wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And it will be to them like a false divination in the eyes of those
        who have sworn oaths with them; but he will bring their iniquity to remembrance,
        that they may be taken.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Because you have made
        your iniquity to be remembered, in that your transgressions are uncovered,
        so that in all your doings your sins appear\u2014because you have come to
        remembrance, you shall be taken in hand."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Now to you, O profane, wicked prince of Israel, whose day has
        come, whose iniquity shall end, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "thus says the Lord God:\u201CRemove the turban, and take off the
        crown;Nothing shall  remain the same.Exalt the humble, and humble the exalted."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: A Sword Against the Ammonites'
      title: A Sword Against the Ammonites
      number: 27
      content: "Overthrown, overthrown,I will make it overthrown!It shall be no longer,Until
        He comes whose right it is,And I will give it to  Him.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, prophesy and say, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord God  concerning the Ammonites and concerning their reproach,\u2019 and
        say:\u2018A sword, a sword is drawn,Polished for slaughter,For consuming,
        for flashing\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: While they see false visions for you,While they divine a lie to you,To
        bring you on the necks of the wicked, the slainWhose day has come,Whose iniquity
        shall end.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u2018Return  it to its sheath.I will judge youIn the place where
        you were created,In the land of your nativity."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: I will pour out My indignation on you;I will blow against you with
        the fire of My wrath,And deliver you into the hands of brutal men who  are
        skillful to destroy.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "You shall be fuel for the fire;Your blood shall be in the midst of
        the land.You shall not be remembered,For I the Lord have spoken.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sins of Jerusalem'
      title: Sins of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNow, son of man, will you judge, will you judge the bloody
        city? Yes, show her all her abominations! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CThe city sheds blood
        in her own midst, that her time may come; and she makes idols within herself
        to defile herself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have become guilty by the blood which you have shed, and have
        defiled yourself with the idols which you have made. You have caused your
        days to draw near, and have come to the  end  of your years; therefore I
        have made you a reproach to the nations, and a mockery to all countries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Those near and those far from you will mock you as infamous and full
        of tumult.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLook, the princes of Israel: each one has used his power to
        shed blood in you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In you they have made light of father and mother; in your midst they
        have oppressed the stranger; in you they have mistreated the fatherless and
        the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have despised My holy things and profaned My Sabbaths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In you are men who slander to cause bloodshed; in you are those who
        eat on the mountains; in your midst they commit lewdness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In you men uncover their fathers\u2019 nakedness; in you they violate
        women who are set apart during their impurity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "One commits abomination with his neighbor\u2019s wife; another lewdly
        defiles his daughter-in-law; and another in you violates his sister, his
        father\u2019s daughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "In you they take bribes to shed blood; you take usury and increase;
        you have made profit from your neighbors by extortion, and have forgotten
        Me,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, therefore, I beat My fists at the dishonest profit
        which you have made, and at the bloodshed which has been in your midst. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Can your heart endure, or can your hands remain strong, in the days
        when I shall deal with you? I, the Lord, have spoken, and will do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will scatter you among the nations, disperse you throughout the
        countries, and remove your filthiness completely from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Israel in the Furnace'
      title: Israel in the Furnace
      number: 16
      content: "You shall defile yourself in the sight of the nations; then you shall
        know that I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CSon of man, the house of Israel has become dross to Me; they
        are all bronze, tin, iron, and lead, in the midst of a furnace; they have
        become dross from silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Because you have all become
        dross, therefore behold, I will gather you into the midst of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As  men gather silver, bronze, iron, lead, and tin into the midst
        of a furnace, to blow fire on it, to melt it; so I will gather you in My
        anger and in My fury, and I will leave you  there and melt you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yes, I will gather you and blow on you with the fire of My wrath,
        and you shall be melted in its midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Israel\u2019s Wicked Leaders"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Wicked Leaders"
      number: 22
      content: "As silver is melted in the midst of a furnace, so shall you be melted
        in its midst; then you shall know that I, the Lord, have poured out My fury
        on you.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSon of man, say to her: \u2018You are a land that is not cleansed
        or rained on in the day of indignation.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The conspiracy of her prophets in her midst is like a roaring lion
        tearing the prey; they have devoured people; they have taken treasure and
        precious things; they have made many widows in her midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Her priests have violated My law and profaned My holy things; they
        have not distinguished between the holy and unholy, nor have they made known
        the  difference between the unclean and the clean; and they have hidden their
        eyes from My Sabbaths, so that I am profaned among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Her princes in her midst are like wolves tearing the prey, to shed
        blood, to destroy people, and to get dishonest gain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Her prophets plastered them with untempered mortar,  seeing false
        visions, and divining lies for them, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord God,\u2019
        when the Lord had not spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The people of the land have used oppressions, committed robbery,
        and mistreated the poor and needy; and they wrongfully oppress the stranger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So I sought for a man among them who would make a wall, and stand
        in the gap before Me on behalf of the land, that I should not destroy it;
        but I found no one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Therefore I have poured out My indignation on them; I have consumed
        them with the fire of My wrath; and I have recompensed their deeds on their
        own heads,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Two Harlot Sisters'
      title: Two Harlot Sisters
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came again to me, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, there were two women,The daughters of one mother."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: They committed harlotry in Egypt,They committed harlotry in their
        youth;Their breasts were there embraced,Their virgin bosom was there pressed.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Older Sister, Samaria'
      title: The Older Sister, Samaria
      number: 4
      content: 'Their names: Oholah the elder and Oholibah her sister;They were Mine,And
        they bore sons and daughters.As  for their names,Samaria is Oholah, and Jerusalem
        is Oholibah.'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201COholah played the harlot even though she was Mine;And she lusted
        for her lovers, the neighboring Assyrians,"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Who  were clothed in purple,Captains and rulers,All of them desirable
        young men,Horsemen riding on horses.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Thus she committed her harlotry with them,All of them choice men of
        Assyria;And with all for whom she lusted,With all their idols, she defiled
        herself.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: She has never given up her harlotry brought  from Egypt,For in her
        youth they had lain with her,Pressed her virgin bosom,And poured out their
        immorality upon her.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore I have delivered herInto the hand of her lovers,Into
        the hand of the Assyrians,For whom she lusted."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Younger Sister, Jerusalem'
      title: The Younger Sister, Jerusalem
      number: 10
      content: They uncovered her nakedness,Took away her sons and daughters,And
        slew her with the sword;She became a byword among women,For they had executed
        judgment on her.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow although her sister Oholibah saw this,  she became more
        corrupt in her lust than she, and in her harlotry more corrupt than her sister\u2019s
        harlotry."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CShe lusted for the neighboring Assyrians,Captains and rulers,Clothed
        most gorgeously,Horsemen riding on horses,All of them desirable young men."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then I saw that she was defiled;Both took the same way.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But she increased her harlotry;She looked at men portrayed on the
        wall,Images of Chaldeans portrayed in vermilion,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Girded with belts around their waists,Flowing turbans on their heads,All
        of them looking like captains,In the manner of the Babylonians of Chaldea,The
        land of their nativity.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: As soon as her eyes saw them,She lusted for themAnd sent messengers
        to them in Chaldea.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThen the Babylonians came to her, into the bed of love,And
        they defiled her with their immorality;So she was defiled by them, and alienated
        herself from them."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: She revealed her harlotry and uncovered her nakedness.Then I alienated
        Myself from her,As I had alienated Myself from her sister.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYet she multiplied her harlotryIn calling to remembrance the
        days of her youth,When she had played the harlot in the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For she lusted for her paramours,Whose flesh is  like the flesh of
        donkeys,And whose issue is  like the issue of horses.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Judgment on Jerusalem'
      title: Judgment on Jerusalem
      number: 21
      content: Thus you called to remembrance the lewdness of your youth,When the
        Egyptians pressed your bosomBecause of your youthful breasts.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CTherefore, Oholibah, thus says the Lord God:\u2018Behold, I
        will stir up your lovers against you,From whom you have alienated yourself,And
        I will bring them against you from every side:"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The Babylonians,All the Chaldeans,Pekod, Shoa, Koa,All the Assyrians
        with them,All of them desirable young men,Governors and rulers,Captains and
        men of renown,All of them riding on horses.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they shall come against youWith chariots, wagons, and war-horses,With
        a horde of people.They shall array against youBuckler, shield, and helmet
        all around.\u2018I will delegate judgment to them,And they shall judge you
        according to their judgments."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I will set My jealousy against you,And they shall deal furiously with
        you;They shall remove your nose and your ears,And your remnant shall fall
        by the sword;They shall take your sons and your daughters,And your remnant
        shall be devoured by fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: They shall also strip you of your clothesAnd take away your beautiful
        jewelry.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018Thus I will make you cease your lewdness and your harlotryBrought
        from the land of Egypt,So that you will not lift your eyes to them,Nor remember
        Egypt anymore.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord God: \u2018Surely I will deliver you
        into the hand of those you hate, into the hand of  those  from whom you alienated
        yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They will deal hatefully with you, take away all you have worked
        for, and leave you naked and bare. The nakedness of your harlotry shall be
        uncovered, both your lewdness and your harlotry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will do these things to you because you have gone as a harlot after
        the Gentiles, because you have become defiled by their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "You have walked in the way of your sister; therefore I will put her
        cup in your hand.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God:\u2018You shall drink of your sister\u2019s
        cup,The deep and wide one;You shall be laughed to scornAnd held in derision;It
        contains much."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: You will be filled with drunkenness and sorrow,The cup of horror and
        desolation,The cup of your sister Samaria.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "You shall drink and drain it,You shall break its shards,And tear
        at your own breasts;For I have spoken,\u2019Says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Both Sisters Judged'
      title: Both Sisters Judged
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God:\u2018Because you have forgotten
        Me and cast Me behind your back,Therefore you shall bear the penaltyOf your
        lewdness and your harlotry.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The Lord also said to me: \u201CSon of man, will you judge Oholah
        and Oholibah? Then declare to them their abominations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For they have committed adultery, and blood is on their hands. They
        have committed adultery with their idols, and even sacrificed their sons
        whom they bore to Me, passing them through the  fire, to devour them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Moreover they have done this to Me: They have defiled My sanctuary
        on the same day and profaned My Sabbaths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: For after they had slain their children for their idols, on the same
        day they came into My sanctuary to profane it; and indeed thus they have
        done in the midst of My house.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CFurthermore you sent for men to come from afar, to whom a messenger
        was sent; and there they came. And you washed yourself for them, painted
        your eyes, and adorned yourself with ornaments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You sat on a stately couch, with a table prepared before it, on which
        you had set My incense and My oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sound of a carefree multitude was with her, and Sabeans were
        brought from the wilderness with men of the common sort, who put bracelets
        on their wrists and beautiful crowns on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then I said concerning her  who  had  grown old in adulteries, \u2018Will
        they commit harlotry with her now, and she with  them?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Yet they went in to her, as men go in to a woman who plays the harlot;
        thus they went in to Oholah and Oholibah, the lewd women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: But righteous men will judge them after the manner of adulteresses,
        and after the manner of women who shed blood, because they are adulteresses,
        and blood is on their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord God: \u2018Bring up an assembly against
        them, give them up to trouble and plunder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The assembly shall stone them with stones and execute them with their
        swords; they shall slay their sons and their daughters, and burn their houses
        with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Thus I will cause lewdness to cease from the land, that all women
        may be taught not to practice your lewdness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "They shall repay you for your lewdness, and you shall pay for your
        idolatrous sins. Then you shall know that I am the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Symbol of the Cooking Pot'
      title: Symbol of the Cooking Pot
      number: 1
      content: 'Again, in the ninth year, in the tenth month, on the tenth day of
        the month, the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, write down the name of the day, this very day\u2014the
        king of Babylon started his siege against Jerusalem this very day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And utter a parable to the rebellious house, and say to them, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord God:\u201CPut on a pot, set it on,And also pour water into
        it."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Gather pieces of  meat in it,Every good piece,The thigh and the shoulder.Fill
        it with choice cuts;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Take the choice of the flock.Also pile fuel bones under it,Make it
        boil well,And let the cuts simmer in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CWoe to the bloody city,To
        the pot whose scum is in it,And whose scum is not gone from it!Bring it out
        piece by piece,On which no lot has fallen."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For her blood is in her midst;She set it on top of a rock;She did
        not pour it on the ground,To cover it with dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "That it may raise up fury and take vengeance,I have set her blood
        on top of a rock,That it may not be covered.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CWoe to the bloody city!I
        too will make the pyre great."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Heap on the wood,Kindle the fire;Cook the meat well,Mix in the spices,And
        let the cuts be burned up.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThen set the pot empty on the coals,That it may become hot
        and its bronze may burn,That  its filthiness may be melted in it,That its
        scum may be consumed."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: She has grown weary with lies,And her great scum has not gone from
        her.Let her scum be in the fire!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: In your filthiness is lewdness.Because I have cleansed you, and you
        were not cleansed,You will not be cleansed of your filthiness anymore,Till
        I have caused My fury to rest upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: "14: The Prophet\u2019s Wife Dies"
      title: "The Prophet\u2019s Wife Dies"
      number: 14
      content: "I, the Lord, have spoken it;It shall come to pass, and I will do
        it;I will not hold back,Nor will I spare,Nor will I relent;According to your
        waysAnd according to your deedsThey will judge you,\u201DSays the Lord God.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Also the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSon of man, behold, I take away from you the desire of your
        eyes with one stroke; yet you shall neither mourn nor weep, nor shall your
        tears run down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Sigh in silence, make no mourning for the dead; bind your turban
        on your head, and put your sandals on your feet; do not cover your lips,
        and do not eat man\u2019s bread of  sorrow.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So I spoke to the people in the morning, and at evening my wife died;
        and the next morning I did as I was commanded.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the people said to me, \u201CWill you not tell us what these
        things  signify to us, that you behave so?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then I answered them, \u201CThe word of the Lord came to me, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Speak to the house of Israel, \u201CThus says the Lord God:
        \u2018Behold, I will profane My sanctuary, your arrogant boast, the desire
        of your eyes, the delight of your soul; and your sons and daughters whom
        you left behind shall fall by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And you shall do as I have done; you shall not cover your lips nor
        eat man\u2019s bread of  sorrow.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Your turbans shall be on your heads and your sandals on your feet;
        you shall neither mourn nor weep, but you shall pine away in your iniquities
        and mourn with one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Thus Ezekiel is a sign to you; according to all that he has done
        you shall do; and when this comes, you shall know that I am the Lord God.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018And you, son of man\u2014will  it not be in the day when I
        take from them their stronghold, their joy and their glory, the desire of
        their eyes, and that on which they set their minds, their sons and their
        daughters: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'that on that day one who escapes will come to you to let you hear
        it with your ears? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "On that day your mouth will be opened to him who has escaped; you
        shall speak and no longer be mute. Thus you will be a sign to them, and they
        shall know that I am the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Ammon'
      title: Proclamation Against Ammon
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face against the Ammonites, and prophesy
        against them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Say to the Ammonites, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord God! Thus says
        the Lord God: \u201CBecause you said, \u2018Aha!\u2019 against My sanctuary
        when it was profaned, and against the land of Israel when it was desolate,
        and against the house of Judah when they went into captivity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'indeed, therefore, I will deliver you as a possession to the men
        of the East, and they shall set their encampments among you and make their
        dwellings among you; they shall eat your fruit, and they shall drink your
        milk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I will make Rabbah a stable for camels and Ammon a resting place
        for flocks. Then you shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018For thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause you clapped your
        hands, stamped your feet, and rejoiced in heart with all your disdain for
        the land of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Proclamation Against Moab'
      title: Proclamation Against Moab
      number: 7
      content: "indeed, therefore, I will stretch out My hand against you, and give
        you as plunder to the nations; I will cut you off from the peoples, and I
        will cause you to perish from the countries; I will destroy you, and you
        shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause Moab and Seir say, \u2018Look!
        The house of Judah is like all the nations,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'therefore, behold, I will clear the territory of Moab of cities,
        of the cities on its frontier, the glory of the country, Beth Jeshimoth,
        Baal Meon, and Kirjathaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'To the men of the East I will give it as a possession, together with
        the Ammonites, that the Ammonites may not be remembered among the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Proclamation Against Edom'
      title: Proclamation Against Edom
      number: 11
      content: "And I will execute judgments upon Moab, and they shall know that
        I am the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause of what Edom did against
        the house of Judah by taking vengeance, and has greatly offended by avenging
        itself on them,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will also stretch out My
        hand against Edom, cut off man and beast from it, and make it desolate from
        Teman; Dedan shall fall by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Proclamation Against Philistia'
      title: Proclamation Against Philistia
      number: 14
      content: "I will lay My vengeance on Edom by the hand of My people Israel,
        that they may do in Edom according to My anger and according to My fury;
        and they shall know My vengeance,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause the Philistines dealt
        vengefully and took vengeance with a spiteful heart, to destroy because of
        the old hatred,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will stretch out My hand
        against the Philistines, and I will cut off the Cherethites and destroy the
        remnant of the seacoast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I will execute great vengeance on them with furious rebukes; and
        they shall know that I am the Lord, when I lay My vengeance upon them.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Tyre'
      title: Proclamation Against Tyre
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in the eleventh year, on the first day of the
        month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, because Tyre has said against Jerusalem, \u2018Aha!
        She is broken who was the gateway of the peoples; now she is turned over
        to me; I shall be filled; she is laid waste.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Behold, I am against
        you, O Tyre, and will cause many nations to come up against you, as the sea
        causes its waves to come up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they shall destroy the walls of Tyre and break down her towers;
        I will also scrape her dust from her, and make her like the top of a rock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It shall be a  place  for spreading nets in the midst of the sea,
        for I have spoken,\u2019 says the Lord God; \u2018it shall become plunder
        for the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Also her daughter villages which are in the fields shall be slain
        by the sword. Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord God: \u2018Behold, I will bring against
        Tyre from the north Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, king of kings, with horses,
        with chariots, and with horsemen, and an army with many people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will slay with the sword your daughter villages in the fields;
        he will heap up a siege mound against you, build a wall against you, and
        raise a defense against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He will direct his battering rams against your walls, and with his
        axes he will break down your towers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Because of the abundance of his horses, their dust will cover you;
        your walls will shake at the noise of the horsemen, the wagons, and the chariots,
        when he enters your gates, as men enter a city that has been breached. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'With the hooves of his horses he will trample all your streets; he
        will slay your people by the sword, and your strong pillars will fall to
        the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They will plunder your riches and pillage your merchandise; they
        will break down your walls and destroy your pleasant houses; they will lay
        your stones, your timber, and your soil in the midst of the water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will put an end to the sound of your songs, and the sound of your
        harps shall be heard no more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will make you like the top of a rock; you shall be a  place  for
        spreading nets, and you shall never be rebuilt, for I the Lord have spoken,\u2019
        says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God to Tyre: \u2018Will the coastlands not
        shake at the sound of your fall, when the wounded cry, when slaughter is
        made in the midst of you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then all the princes of the sea will come down from their thrones,
        lay aside their robes, and take off their embroidered garments; they will
        clothe themselves with trembling; they will sit on the ground, tremble every
        moment, and be astonished at you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they will take up a lamentation for you, and say to you:\u201CHow
        you have perished,O one inhabited by seafaring men,O renowned city,Who was
        strong at sea,She and her inhabitants,Who caused their terror to  be on all
        her inhabitants!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now the coastlands tremble on the day of your fall;Yes, the coastlands
        by the sea are troubled at your departure.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord God: \u2018When I make you a desolate
        city, like cities that are not inhabited, when I bring the deep upon you,
        and great waters cover you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'then I will bring you down with those who descend into the Pit, to
        the people of old, and I will make you dwell in the lowest part of the earth,
        in places desolate from antiquity, with those who go down to the Pit, so
        that you may never be inhabited; and I shall establish glory in the land
        of the living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will make you a terror, and you shall  be no more;  though you
        are sought for, you will never be found again,\u2019 says the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lamentation for Tyre'
      title: Lamentation for Tyre
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came again to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNow, son of man, take up a lamentation for Tyre, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say to Tyre, \u2018You who are situated at the entrance of the
        sea, merchant of the peoples on many coastlands, thus says the Lord God:\u201CO
        Tyre, you have said,\u2018I am perfect in beauty.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Your borders are in the midst of the seas.Your builders have perfected
        your beauty.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They made all your planks of fir trees from Senir;They took a cedar
        from Lebanon to make you a mast.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Of  oaks from Bashan they made your oars;The company of Ashurites
        have inlaid your planksWith ivory from the coasts of Cyprus.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Fine embroidered linen from Egypt was what you spread for your sail;Blue
        and purple from the coasts of Elishah was what covered you.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CInhabitants of Sidon and Arvad were your oarsmen;Your wise
        men, O Tyre, were in you;They became your pilots."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Elders of Gebal and its wise menWere in you to caulk your seams;All
        the ships of the seaAnd their oarsmen were in youTo market your merchandise.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThose from Persia, Lydia, and LibyaWere in your army as men
        of war;They hung shield and helmet in you;They gave splendor to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Men of Arvad with your army were on your walls all around,And the
        men of Gammad were in your towers;They hung their shields on your walls all
        around;They made your beauty perfect.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTarshish was your merchant because of your many luxury goods.
        They gave you silver, iron, tin, and lead for your goods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Javan, Tubal, and Meshech were your traders. They bartered human
        lives and vessels of bronze for your merchandise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Those from the house of Togarmah traded for your wares with horses,
        steeds, and mules. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The men of Dedan were your traders; many isles were the market of
        your hand. They brought you ivory tusks and ebony as payment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Syria was your merchant because of the abundance of goods you made.
        They gave you for your wares emeralds, purple, embroidery, fine linen, corals,
        and rubies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Judah and the land of Israel were your traders. They traded for your
        merchandise wheat of Minnith, millet, honey, oil, and balm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Damascus was your merchant because of the abundance of goods you
        made, because of your many luxury items, with the wine of Helbon and with
        white wool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Dan and Javan paid for your wares, traversing back and forth. Wrought
        iron, cassia, and cane were among your merchandise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Dedan was your merchant in saddlecloths for riding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Arabia and all the princes of Kedar were your regular merchants.
        They traded with you in lambs, rams, and goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The merchants of Sheba and Raamah were your merchants. They traded
        for your wares the choicest spices, all kinds of precious stones, and gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Haran, Canneh, Eden, the merchants of Sheba, Assyria, and Chilmad
        were your merchants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "These were your merchants in choice items\u2014in purple clothes,
        in embroidered garments, in chests of multicolored apparel, in sturdy woven
        cords, which were in your marketplace."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThe ships of Tarshish were carriers of your merchandise.You
        were filled and very glorious in the midst of the seas."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Your oarsmen brought you into many waters,But the east wind broke
        you in the midst of the seas.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CYour riches, wares, and merchandise,Your mariners and pilots,Your
        caulkers and merchandisers,All your men of war who are in you,And the entire
        company which is in your midst,Will fall into the midst of the seas on the
        day of your ruin."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The common-land will shake at the sound of the cry of your pilots.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAll who handle the oar,The mariners,All the pilots of the seaWill
        come down from their ships and stand on the shore."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: They will make their voice heard because of you;They will cry bitterly
        and cast dust on their heads;They will roll about in ashes;
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: They will shave themselves completely bald because of you,Gird themselves
        with sackcloth,And weep for youWith bitterness of heart and bitter wailing.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "In their wailing for youThey will take up a lamentation,And lament
        for you:\u2018What city  is like Tyre,Destroyed in the midst of the sea?"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u2018When your wares went out by sea,You satisfied many people;You
        enriched the kings of the earthWith your many luxury goods and your merchandise."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: But you are broken by the seas in the depths of the waters;Your merchandise
        and the entire company will fall in your midst.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: All the inhabitants of the isles will be astonished at you;Their kings
        will be greatly afraid,And their countenance will be troubled.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The merchants among the peoples will hiss at you;You will become
        a horror, and be no more forever.\u2019 \u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against the King of Tyre'
      title: Proclamation Against the King of Tyre
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me again, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, say to the prince of Tyre, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord God:\u201CBecause your heart is  lifted up,And you say, \u2018I am a
        god,I sit in the seat of gods,In the midst of the seas,\u2019Yet you are
        a man, and not a god,Though you set your heart as the heart of a god"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: (Behold, you are wiser than Daniel!There is no secret that can be
        hidden from you!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: With your wisdom and your understandingYou have gained riches for
        yourself,And gathered gold and silver into your treasuries;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "By your great wisdom in trade you have increased your riches,And
        your heart is lifted up because of your riches),\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CBecause you have set
        your heart as the heart of a god,"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Behold, therefore, I will bring strangers against you,The most terrible
        of the nations;And they shall draw their swords against the beauty of your
        wisdom,And defile your splendor.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They shall throw you down into the Pit,And you shall die the death
        of the slainIn the midst of the seas.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWill you still say before him who slays you,\u2018I am a god\u2019?But
        you shall  be a man, and not a god,In the hand of him who slays you."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Lamentation for the King of Tyre'
      title: Lamentation for the King of Tyre
      number: 10
      content: "You shall die the death of the uncircumcisedBy the hand of aliens;For
        I have spoken,\u201D says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSon of man, take up a lamentation for the king of Tyre, and
        say to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CYou were the seal of perfection,Full
        of wisdom and perfect in beauty."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You were in Eden, the garden of God;Every precious stone was your
        covering:The sardius, topaz, and diamond,Beryl, onyx, and jasper,Sapphire,
        turquoise, and emerald with gold.The workmanship of your timbrels and pipesWas
        prepared for you on the day you were created.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou were the anointed cherub who covers;I established you;You
        were on the holy mountain of God;You walked back and forth in the midst of
        fiery stones."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You were perfect in your ways from the day you were created,Till iniquity
        was found in you.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBy the abundance of your tradingYou became filled with violence
        within,And you sinned;Therefore I cast you as a profane thingOut of the mountain
        of God;And I destroyed you, O covering cherub,From the midst of the fiery
        stones."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYour heart was lifted up because of your beauty;You corrupted
        your wisdom for the sake of your splendor;I cast you to the ground,I laid
        you before kings,That they might gaze at you."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou defiled your sanctuariesBy the multitude of your iniquities,By
        the iniquity of your trading;Therefore I brought fire from your midst;It
        devoured you,And I turned you to ashes upon the earthIn the sight of all
        who saw you."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Proclamation Against Sidon'
      title: Proclamation Against Sidon
      number: 19
      content: "All who knew you among the peoples are astonished at you;You have
        become a horror,And shall  be no more forever.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face toward Sidon, and prophesy against
        her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, I am against
        you, O Sidon;I will be glorified in your midst;And they shall know that I
        am the Lord,When I execute judgments in her and am hallowed in her."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For I will send pestilence upon her,And blood in her streets;The wounded
        shall be judged in her midstBy the sword against her on every side;Then they
        shall know that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Israel\u2019s Future Blessing"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Future Blessing"
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd there shall no longer be a pricking brier or a painful
        thorn for the house of Israel from among all who  are around them, who despise
        them. Then they shall know that I am the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CWhen I have gathered the house
        of Israel from the peoples among whom they are scattered, and am hallowed
        in them in the sight of the Gentiles, then they will dwell in their own land
        which I gave to My servant Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they will dwell safely there, build houses, and plant vineyards;
        yes, they will dwell securely, when I execute judgments on all those around
        them who despise them. Then they shall know that I am the Lord their God.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Egypt'
      title: Proclamation Against Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'In the tenth year, in the tenth month, on the twelfth day of the
        month, the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face against Pharaoh king of Egypt, and
        prophesy against him, and against all Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Speak, and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, I am against
        you,O Pharaoh king of Egypt,O great monster who lies in the midst of his
        rivers,Who has said, \u2018My River is my own;I have made it for myself.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But I will put hooks in your jaws,And cause the fish of your rivers
        to stick to your scales;I will bring you up out of the midst of your rivers,And
        all the fish in your rivers will stick to your scales.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I will leave you in the wilderness,You and all the fish of your rivers;You
        shall fall on the open field;You shall not be picked up or gathered.I have
        given you as foodTo the beasts of the fieldAnd to the birds of the heavens.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThen all the inhabitants of EgyptShall know that I am the Lord,Because
        they have been a staff of reed to the house of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When they took hold of you with the hand,You broke and tore all their
        shoulders;When they leaned on you,You broke and made all their backs quiver.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CSurely I will bring
        a sword upon you and cut off from you man and beast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the land of Egypt shall become desolate and waste; then they
        will know that I am the Lord, because he said, \u2018The River is mine, and
        I have made it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Indeed, therefore, I am against you and against your rivers, and
        I will make the land of Egypt utterly waste and desolate, from Migdol to
        Syene, as far as the border of Ethiopia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Neither foot of man shall pass through it nor foot of beast pass
        through it, and it shall be uninhabited forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will make the land of Egypt desolate in the midst of the countries
        that  are desolate; and among the cities that  are laid waste, her cities
        shall be desolate forty years; and I will scatter the Egyptians among the
        nations and disperse them throughout the countries.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Yet, thus says the Lord God: \u201CAt the end of forty years
        I will gather the Egyptians from the peoples among whom they were scattered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will bring back the captives of Egypt and cause them to return
        to the land of Pathros, to the land of their origin, and there they shall
        be a lowly kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It shall be the lowliest of kingdoms; it shall never again exalt
        itself above the nations, for I will diminish them so that they will not
        rule over the nations anymore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Babylonia Will Plunder Egypt'
      title: Babylonia Will Plunder Egypt
      number: 16
      content: "No longer shall it be the confidence of the house of Israel, but
        will remind them of their iniquity when they turned to follow them. Then
        they shall know that I am the Lord God.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it came to pass in the twenty-seventh year, in the first month,
        on the first day of the month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CSon of man, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon caused his army
        to labor strenuously against Tyre; every head was made bald, and every shoulder
        rubbed raw; yet neither he nor his army received wages from Tyre, for the
        labor which they expended on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Surely I will give the land
        of Egypt to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; he shall take away her wealth,
        carry off her spoil, and remove her pillage; and that will be the wages for
        his army. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I have given him the land of Egypt for his labor, because they worked
        for Me,\u2019 says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018In that day I will cause the horn of the house of Israel to
        spring forth, and I will open your mouth to speak in their midst. Then they
        shall know that I am the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Egypt and Her Allies Will Fall'
      title: Egypt and Her Allies Will Fall
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to me again, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, prophesy and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CWail,
        \u2018Woe to the day!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the day is near,Even the day of the Lord  is near;It will be a
        day of clouds, the time of the Gentiles.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The sword shall come upon Egypt,And great anguish shall be in Ethiopia,When
        the slain fall in Egypt,And they take away her wealth,And her foundations
        are broken down.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CEthiopia, Libya, Lydia, all the mingled people, Chub, and the
        men of the lands who are allied, shall fall with them by the sword.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord:\u201CThose who uphold Egypt shall fall,And
        the pride of her power shall come down.From Migdol to SyeneThose within her
        shall fall by the sword,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThey shall be desolate in the midst of the desolate countries,And
        her cities shall be in the midst of the cities that  are laid waste."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then they will know that I am the Lord,When I have set a fire in EgyptAnd
        all her helpers are destroyed.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "On that day messengers shall go forth from Me in shipsTo make the
        careless Ethiopians afraid,And great anguish shall come upon them,As on the
        day of Egypt;For indeed it is coming!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CI will also make a multitude of
        Egypt to ceaseBy the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He and his people with him, the most terrible of the nations,Shall
        be brought to destroy the land;They shall draw their swords against Egypt,And
        fill the land with the slain.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will make the rivers dry,And sell the land into the hand of the
        wicked;I will make the land waste, and all that is in it,By the hand of aliens.I,
        the Lord, have spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CI will also destroy the idols,And
        cause the images to cease from Noph;There shall no longer be princes from
        the land of Egypt;I will put fear in the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I will make Pathros desolate,Set fire to Zoan,And execute judgments
        in No.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will pour My fury on Sin, the strength of Egypt;I will cut off the
        multitude of No,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And set a fire in Egypt;Sin shall have great pain,No shall be split
        open,And Noph shall  be  in distress daily.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The young men of Aven and Pi Beseth shall fall by the sword,And these
        cities shall go into captivity.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: At Tehaphnehes the day shall also be darkened,When I break the yokes
        of Egypt there.And her arrogant strength shall cease in her;As for her, a
        cloud shall cover her,And her daughters shall go into captivity.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Proclamation Against Pharaoh'
      title: Proclamation Against Pharaoh
      number: 19
      content: "Thus I will execute judgments on Egypt,Then they shall know that
        I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it came to pass in the eleventh year, in the first month, on
        the seventh day of the month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSon of man, I have broken the arm of Pharaoh king of Egypt;
        and see, it has not been bandaged for healing, nor a splint put on to bind
        it, to make it strong enough to hold a sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Surely I am  against Pharaoh
        king of Egypt, and will break his arms, both the strong one and the one that
        was broken; and I will make the sword fall out of his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I will scatter the Egyptians among the nations, and disperse them
        throughout the countries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I will strengthen the arms of the king of Babylon and put My sword
        in his hand; but I will break Pharaoh\u2019s arms, and he will groan before
        him with the groanings of a mortally wounded man.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Thus I will strengthen the arms of the king of Babylon, but the arms
        of Pharaoh shall fall down; they shall know that I am the Lord, when I put
        My sword into the hand of the king of Babylon and he stretches it out against
        the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will scatter the Egyptians among the nations and disperse them
        throughout the countries. Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Egypt Cut Down Like a Great Tree'
      title: Egypt Cut Down Like a Great Tree
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the eleventh year, in the third month, on
        the first day of the month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, say to Pharaoh king of Egypt and to his multitude:\u2018Whom
        are you like in your greatness?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Indeed Assyria was a cedar in Lebanon,With fine branches that shaded
        the forest,And of high stature;And its top was among the thick boughs.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The waters made it grow;Underground waters gave it height,With their
        rivers running around the place where it was planted,And sent out rivulets
        to all the trees of the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Therefore its height was exalted above all the trees of the
        field;Its boughs were multiplied,And its branches became long because of
        the abundance of water,As it sent them out."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: All the birds of the heavens made their nests in its boughs;Under
        its branches all the beasts of the field brought forth their young;And in
        its shadow all great nations made their home.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Thus it was beautiful in greatness and in the length of its
        branches,Because its roots reached to abundant waters."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The cedars in the garden of God could not hide it;The fir trees were
        not like its boughs,And the chestnut trees were not like its branches;No
        tree in the garden of God was like it in beauty.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I made it beautiful with a multitude of branches,So that all the
        trees of Eden envied it,That were in the garden of God.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Because you have increased
        in height, and it set its top among the thick boughs, and its heart was lifted
        up in its height, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'therefore I will deliver it into the hand of the mighty one of the
        nations, and he shall surely deal with it; I have driven it out for its wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And aliens, the most terrible of the nations, have cut it down and
        left it; its branches have fallen on the mountains and in all the valleys;
        its boughs lie broken by all the rivers of the land; and all the peoples
        of the earth have gone from under its shadow and left it.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018On its ruin will remain all the birds of the heavens,And all
        the beasts of the field will come to its branches\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018So that no trees by the waters may ever again exalt themselves
        for their height, nor set their tops among the thick boughs, that no tree
        which drinks water may ever be high enough to reach up to them.\u2018For
        they have all been delivered to death,To the depths of the earth,Among the
        children of men who go down to the Pit.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God: \u2018In the day when it went down
        to hell, I caused mourning. I covered the deep because of it. I restrained
        its rivers, and the great waters were held back. I caused Lebanon to mourn
        for it, and all the trees of the field wilted because of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I made the nations shake at the sound of its fall, when I cast it
        down to hell together with those who descend into the Pit; and all the trees
        of Eden, the choice and best of Lebanon, all that drink water, were comforted
        in the depths of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: They also went down to hell with it, with those slain by the sword;
        and those  who  were its strong arm dwelt in its shadows among the nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018To which of the trees in Eden will you then be likened in glory
        and greatness? Yet you shall be brought down with the trees of Eden to the
        depths of the earth; you shall lie in the midst of the uncircumcised, with
        those slain by the sword. This is Pharaoh and all his multitude,\u2019 says
        the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lamentation for Pharaoh and Egypt'
      title: Lamentation for Pharaoh and Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in the twelfth year, in the twelfth month, on
        the first day of the month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, take up a lamentation for Pharaoh king of Egypt,
        and say to him:\u2018You are like a young lion among the nations,And you
        are like a monster in the seas,Bursting forth in your rivers,Troubling the
        waters with your feet,And fouling their rivers."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CI will therefore spread My net
        over you with a company of many people,And they will draw you up in My net."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Then I will leave you on the land;I will cast you out on the open
        fields,And cause to settle on you all the birds of the heavens.And with you
        I will fill the beasts of the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I will lay your flesh on the mountains,And fill the valleys with your
        carcass.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI will also water the land with the flow of your blood,Even
        to the mountains;And the riverbeds will be full of you."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When I put out your light,I will cover the heavens, and make its stars
        dark;I will cover the sun with a cloud,And the moon shall not give her light.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All the bright lights of the heavens I will make dark over you,And
        bring darkness upon your land,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018I will also trouble the hearts of many peoples, when I bring
        your destruction among the nations, into the countries which you have not
        known. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yes, I will make many peoples astonished at you, and their kings shall
        be horribly afraid of you when I brandish My sword before them; and they
        shall tremble every moment, every man for his own life, in the day of your
        fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018For thus says the Lord God: \u201CThe sword of the king of
        Babylon shall come upon you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "By the swords of the mighty warriors, all of them the most terrible
        of the nations, I will cause your multitude to fall.\u201CThey shall plunder
        the pomp of Egypt,And all its multitude shall be destroyed."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Also I will destroy all its animalsFrom beside its great waters;The
        foot of man shall muddy them no more,Nor shall the hooves of animals muddy
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then I will make their waters clear,And make their rivers run like
        oil,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhen I make the land of Egypt desolate,And the country is destitute
        of all that once filled it,When I strike all who dwell in it,Then they shall
        know that I am the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Egypt and Others Consigned to the Pit'
      title: Egypt and Others Consigned to the Pit
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis is the lamentationWith which they shall lament her;The
        daughters of the nations shall lament her;They shall lament for her, for
        Egypt,And for all her multitude,\u201DSays the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It came to pass also in the twelfth year, on the fifteenth day of
        the month, that the word of the Lord came to me, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CSon of man, wail over the multitude of Egypt,And cast them
        down to the depths of the earth,Her and the daughters of the famous nations,With
        those who go down to the Pit:"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018Whom do you surpass in beauty?Go down, be placed with the uncircumcised.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThey shall fall in the midst of those slain by the sword;She
        is delivered to the sword,Drawing her and all her multitudes."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The strong among the mightyShall speak to him out of the midst of
        hellWith those who help him:\u2018They have gone down,They lie with the uncircumcised,
        slain by the sword.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAssyria  is there, and all her company,With their graves all
        around her,All of them slain, fallen by the sword."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Her graves are set in the recesses of the Pit,And her company is all
        around her grave,All of them slain, fallen by the sword,Who caused terror
        in the land of the living.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThere is  Elam and all her multitude,All around her grave,All
        of them slain, fallen by the sword,Who have gone down uncircumcised to the
        lower parts of the earth,Who caused their terror in the land of the living;Now
        they bear their shame with those who go down to the Pit."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: They have set her bed in the midst of the slain,With all her multitude,With
        her graves all around it,All of them uncircumcised, slain by the sword;Though
        their terror was causedIn the land of the living,Yet they bear their shameWith
        those who go down to the Pit;It was put in the midst of the slain.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThere are  Meshech and Tubal and all their multitudes,With
        all their graves around it,All of them uncircumcised, slain by the sword,Though
        they caused their terror in the land of the living."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: They do not lie with the mightyWho  are fallen of the uncircumcised,Who
        have gone down to hell with their weapons of war;They have laid their swords
        under their heads,But their iniquities will be on their bones,Because of
        the terror of the mighty in the land of the living.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Yes, you shall be broken in the midst of the uncircumcised,And lie
        with those slain by the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThere is  Edom,Her kings and all her princes,Who despite their
        mightAre laid beside those slain by the sword;They shall lie with the uncircumcised,And
        with those who go down to the Pit."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: There are the princes of the north,All of them, and all the Sidonians,Who
        have gone down with the slainIn shame at the terror which they caused by
        their might;They lie uncircumcised with those slain by the sword,And bear
        their shame with those who go down to the Pit.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CPharaoh will see themAnd be comforted over all his multitude,Pharaoh
        and all his army,Slain by the sword,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor I have caused My terror in the land of the living;And he
        shall be placed in the midst of the uncircumcisedWith those slain by the
        sword,Pharaoh and all his multitude,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Watchman and His Message'
      title: The Watchman and His Message
      number: 1
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, speak to the children of your people, and say to
        them: \u2018When I bring the sword upon a land, and the people of the land
        take a man from their territory and make him their watchman, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'when he sees the sword coming upon the land, if he blows the trumpet
        and warns the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'then whoever hears the sound of the trumpet and does not take warning,
        if the sword comes and takes him away, his blood shall be on his own head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He heard the sound of the trumpet, but did not take warning; his
        blood shall be upon himself. But he who takes warning will save his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But if the watchman sees the sword coming and does not blow the trumpet,
        and the people are not warned, and the sword comes and takes any person from
        among them, he is taken away in his iniquity; but his blood I will require
        at the watchman\u2019s hand.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CSo you, son of man: I have made you a watchman for the house
        of Israel; therefore you shall hear a word from My mouth and warn them for
        Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When I say to the wicked, \u2018O wicked man, you shall surely die!\u2019
        and you do not speak to warn the wicked from his way, that wicked man shall
        die in his iniquity; but his blood I will require at your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Nevertheless if you warn the wicked to turn from his way, and he does
        not turn from his way, he shall die in his iniquity; but you have delivered
        your soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore you, O son of man, say to the house of Israel: \u2018Thus
        you say, \u201CIf our transgressions and our sins lie upon us, and we pine
        away in them, how can we then live?\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: The Fairness of God\u2019s Judgment"
      title: "The Fairness of God\u2019s Judgment"
      number: 11
      content: "Say to them: \u2018As I live,\u2019 says the Lord God, \u2018I have
        no pleasure in the death of the wicked, but that the wicked turn from his
        way and live. Turn, turn from your evil ways! For why should you die, O house
        of Israel?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore you, O son of man, say to the children of your people:
        \u2018The righteousness of the righteous man shall not deliver him in the
        day of his transgression; as for the wickedness of the wicked, he shall not
        fall because of it in the day that he turns from his wickedness; nor shall
        the righteous be able to live because of his  righteousness in the day that
        he sins.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When I say to the righteous that he shall surely live, but he trusts
        in his own righteousness and commits iniquity, none of his righteous works
        shall be remembered; but because of the iniquity that he has committed, he
        shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Again, when I say to the wicked, \u2018You shall surely die,\u2019
        if he turns from his sin and does what is lawful and right, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'if the wicked restores the pledge, gives back what he has stolen,
        and walks in the statutes of life without committing iniquity, he shall surely
        live; he shall not die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: None of his sins which he has committed shall be remembered against
        him; he has done what is lawful and right; he shall surely live.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYet the children of your people say, \u2018The way of the Lord
        is not fair.\u2019 But it is their way which is not fair! "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the righteous turns from his righteousness and commits iniquity,
        he shall die because of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when the wicked turns from his wickedness and does what is lawful
        and right, he shall live because of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 20
      content: "Yet you say, \u2018The way of the Lord is not fair.\u2019 O house
        of Israel, I will judge every one of you according to his own ways.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And it came to pass in the twelfth year of our captivity, in the
        tenth month, on the fifth day of the month, that one who had escaped from
        Jerusalem came to me and said, \u201CThe city has been captured!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "22: The Cause of Judah\u2019s Ruin"
      title: "The Cause of Judah\u2019s Ruin"
      number: 22
      content: Now the hand of the Lord had been upon me the evening before the man
        came who had escaped. And He had opened my mouth; so when he came to me in
        the morning, my mouth was opened, and I was no longer mute.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSon of man, they who inhabit those ruins in the land of Israel
        are saying, \u2018Abraham was only one, and he inherited the land. But we
        are many; the land has been given to us as a possession.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTherefore say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CYou
        eat meat with blood, you lift up your eyes toward your idols, and shed blood.
        Should you then possess the land? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "You rely on your sword, you commit abominations, and you defile one
        another\u2019s wives. Should you then possess the land?\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CSay thus to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CAs I
        live, surely those who are in the ruins shall fall by the sword, and the
        one who is in the open field I will give to the beasts to be devoured, and
        those who are in the strongholds and caves shall die of the pestilence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For I will make the land most desolate, her arrogant strength shall
        cease, and the mountains of Israel shall be so desolate that no one will
        pass through. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Hearing and Not Doing'
      title: Hearing and Not Doing
      number: 29
      content: "Then they shall know that I am the Lord, when I have made the land
        most desolate because of all their abominations which they have committed.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAs for you, son of man, the children of your people are talking
        about you beside the walls and in the doors of the houses; and they speak
        to one another, everyone saying to his brother, \u2018Please come and hear
        what the word is that comes from the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So they come to you as people do, they sit before you as My people,
        and they hear your words, but they do not do them; for with their mouth they
        show much love, but  their hearts pursue their own gain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Indeed you are to them as a very lovely song of one who has a pleasant
        voice and can play well on an instrument; for they hear your words, but they
        do not do them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And when this comes to pass\u2014surely it will come\u2014then they
        will know that a prophet has been among them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Irresponsible Shepherds'
      title: Irresponsible Shepherds
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel, prophesy
        and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God to the shepherds: \u201CWoe
        to the shepherds of Israel who feed themselves! Should not the shepherds
        feed the flocks? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You eat the fat and clothe yourselves with the wool; you slaughter
        the fatlings, but you do not feed the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The weak you have not strengthened, nor have you healed those who
        were sick, nor bound up the broken, nor brought back what was driven away,
        nor sought what was lost; but with force and cruelty you have ruled them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they were scattered because there  was no shepherd; and they became
        food for all the beasts of the field when they were scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "My sheep wandered through all the mountains, and on every high hill;
        yes, My flock was scattered over the whole face of the earth, and no one
        was seeking or searching for  them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Therefore, you shepherds, hear the word of the Lord: "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Csurely because My
        flock became a prey, and My flock became food for every beast of the field,
        because there  was no shepherd, nor did My shepherds search for My flock,
        but the shepherds fed themselves and did not feed My flock\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'therefore, O shepherds, hear the word of the Lord! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: God, the True Shepherd'
      title: God, the True Shepherd
      number: 10
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBehold, I am  against the shepherds,
        and I will require My flock at their hand; I will cause them to cease feeding
        the sheep, and the shepherds shall feed themselves no more; for I will deliver
        My flock from their mouths, that they may no longer be food for them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018For thus says the Lord God: \u201CIndeed I Myself will search
        for My sheep and seek them out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As a shepherd seeks out his flock on the day he is among his scattered
        sheep, so will I seek out My sheep and deliver them from all the places where
        they were scattered on a cloudy and dark day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will bring them out from the peoples and gather them from the
        countries, and will bring them to their own land; I will feed them on the
        mountains of Israel, in the valleys and in all the inhabited places of the
        country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will feed them in good pasture, and their fold shall be on the
        high mountains of Israel. There they shall lie down in a good fold and feed
        in rich pasture on the mountains of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will feed My flock, and I will make them lie down,\u201D says the
        Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CI will seek what was lost and bring back what was driven away,
        bind up the broken and strengthen what was sick; but I will destroy the fat
        and the strong, and feed them in judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018And as  for you, O My flock, thus says the Lord God: \u201CBehold,
        I shall judge between sheep and sheep, between rams and goats. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Is  it too little for you to have eaten up the good pasture, that
        you must tread down with your feet the residue of your pasture\u2014and to
        have drunk of the clear waters, that you must foul the residue with your
        feet? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And as  for My flock, they eat what you have trampled with your feet,
        and they drink what you have fouled with your feet.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord God to them: \u201CBehold, I Myself
        will judge between the fat and the lean sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Because you have pushed with side and shoulder, butted all the weak
        ones with your horns, and scattered them abroad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'therefore I will save My flock, and they shall no longer be a prey;
        and I will judge between sheep and sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will establish one shepherd over them, and he shall feed them\u2014My
        servant David. He shall feed them and be their shepherd. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And I, the Lord, will be their God, and My servant David a prince
        among them; I, the Lord, have spoken.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI will make a covenant of peace with them, and cause wild beasts
        to cease from the land; and they will dwell safely in the wilderness and
        sleep in the woods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will make them and the places all around My hill a blessing; and
        I will cause showers to come down in their season; there shall be showers
        of blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the trees of the field shall yield their fruit, and the earth
        shall yield her increase. They shall be safe in their land; and they shall
        know that I am the Lord, when I have broken the bands of their yoke and delivered
        them from the hand of those who enslaved them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they shall no longer be a prey for the nations, nor shall beasts
        of the land devour them; but they shall dwell safely, and no one shall make
        them afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I will raise up for them a garden of renown, and they shall no longer
        be consumed with hunger in the land, nor bear the shame of the Gentiles anymore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus they shall know that I, the Lord their God, am with them, and
        they, the house of Israel, are  My people,\u201D says the Lord God.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou are My flock, the flock of My pasture; you are men, and
        I am your God,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Mount Seir'
      title: Judgment on Mount Seir
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face against Mount Seir and prophesy against
        it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say to it, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, O Mount
        Seir, I am against you;I will stretch out My hand against you,And make you
        most desolate;"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I shall lay your cities waste,And you shall be desolate.Then you shall
        know that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBecause you have had an ancient hatred, and have shed the 
        blood  of the children of Israel by the power of the sword at the time of
        their calamity, when their iniquity came  to  an end, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "therefore, as I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201CI will prepare
        you for blood, and blood shall pursue you; since you have not hated blood,
        therefore blood shall pursue you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus I will make Mount Seir most desolate, and cut off from it the
        one who leaves and the one who returns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I will fill its mountains with the slain; on your hills and in
        your valleys and in all your ravines those who are slain by the sword shall
        fall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: I will make you perpetually desolate, and your cities shall be uninhabited;
        then you shall know that I am the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CBecause you have said, \u2018These two nations and these two
        countries shall be mine, and we will possess them,\u2019 although the Lord
        was there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "therefore, as I live,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201CI will do according
        to your anger and according to the envy which you showed in your hatred against
        them; and I will make Myself known among them when I judge you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then you shall know that I am the Lord. I have heard all your blasphemies
        which you have spoken against the mountains of Israel, saying, \u2018They
        are desolate; they are given to us to consume.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus with your mouth you have boasted against Me and multiplied your
        words against Me; I have heard them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CThe whole earth will rejoice
        when I make you desolate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "As you rejoiced because the inheritance of the house of Israel was
        desolate, so I will do to you; you shall be desolate, O Mount Seir, as well
        as all of Edom\u2014all of it! Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Blessing on Israel'
      title: Blessing on Israel
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, prophesy to the mountains of Israel, and
        say, \u2018O mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause the enemy has said of you,
        \u2018Aha! The ancient heights have become our possession,\u2019 \u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "therefore prophesy, and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause
        they made you desolate and swallowed you up on every side, so that you became
        the possession of the rest of the nations, and you are taken up by the lips
        of talkers and slandered by the people\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "therefore, O mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord God!
        Thus says the Lord God to the mountains, the hills, the rivers, the valleys,
        the desolate wastes, and the cities that have been forsaken, which became
        plunder and mockery to the rest of the nations all around\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CSurely I have spoken in My
        burning jealousy against the rest of the nations and against all Edom, who
        gave My land to themselves as a possession, with wholehearted joy and spiteful
        minds, in order to plunder its open country.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CTherefore prophesy concerning the land of Israel, and say to
        the mountains, the hills, the rivers, and the valleys, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord God: \u201CBehold, I have spoken in My jealousy and My fury, because
        you have borne the shame of the nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CI have raised My hand in
        an oath that surely the nations that are around you shall bear their own
        shame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you, O mountains of Israel, you shall shoot forth your branches
        and yield your fruit to My people Israel, for they are about to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For indeed I am for you, and I will turn to you, and you shall be
        tilled and sown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will multiply men upon you, all the house of Israel, all of it;
        and the cities shall be inhabited and the ruins rebuilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will multiply upon you man and beast; and they shall increase and
        bear young; I will make you inhabited as in former times, and do better for 
        you than at your beginnings. Then you shall know that I am the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Yes, I will cause men to walk on you, My people Israel; they shall
        take possession of you, and you shall be their inheritance; no more shall
        you bereave them of  children.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CBecause they say to you, \u2018You
        devour men and bereave your nation of  children,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "therefore you shall devour men no more, nor bereave your nation anymore,\u201D
        says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Renewal of Israel'
      title: The Renewal of Israel
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CNor will I let you hear the taunts of the nations anymore,
        nor bear the reproach of the peoples anymore, nor shall you cause your nation
        to stumble anymore,\u201D says the Lord God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CSon of man, when the house of Israel dwelt in their own land,
        they defiled it by their own ways and deeds; to Me their way was like the
        uncleanness of a woman in her customary impurity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore I poured out My fury on them for the blood they had shed
        on the land, and for their idols with  which they had defiled it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So I scattered them among the nations, and they were dispersed throughout
        the countries; I judged them according to their ways and their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When they came to the nations, wherever they went, they profaned
        My holy name\u2014when they said of them, \u2018These are the people of the
        Lord, and yet they have gone out of His land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But I had concern for My holy name, which the house of Israel had
        profaned among the nations wherever they went.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CTherefore say to the house of Israel, \u2018Thus says the Lord
        God: \u201CI do not do this for your sake, O house of Israel, but for My
        holy name\u2019s sake, which you have profaned among the nations wherever
        you went. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And I will sanctify My great name, which has been profaned among
        the nations, which you have profaned in their midst; and the nations shall
        know that I am the Lord,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cwhen I am hallowed
        in you before their eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For I will take you from among the nations, gather you out of all
        countries, and bring you into your own land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then I will sprinkle clean water on you, and you shall be clean;
        I will cleanse you from all your filthiness and from all your idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will give you a new heart and put a new spirit within you; I will
        take the heart of stone out of your flesh and give you a heart of flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'I will put My Spirit within you and cause you to walk in My statutes,
        and you will keep My judgments and do them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then you shall dwell in the land that I gave to your fathers; you
        shall be My people, and I will be your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I will deliver you from all your uncleannesses. I will call for the
        grain and multiply it, and bring no famine upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And I will multiply the fruit of your trees and the increase of your
        fields, so that you need never again bear the reproach of famine among the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then you will remember your evil ways and your deeds that were not
        good; and you will loathe yourselves in your own sight, for your iniquities
        and your abominations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Not for your sake do I do this,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Clet
        it be known to you. Be ashamed and confounded for your own ways, O house
        of Israel!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201COn the day that I cleanse you
        from all your iniquities, I will also enable you to dwell in the cities,
        and the ruins shall be rebuilt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The desolate land shall be tilled instead of lying desolate in the
        sight of all who pass by. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So they will say, \u2018This land that was desolate has become like
        the garden of Eden; and the wasted, desolate, and ruined cities are  now
        fortified and inhabited.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the nations which are left all around you shall know that I,
        the Lord, have rebuilt the ruined places and planted what was desolate. I,
        the Lord, have spoken it, and I will do it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CI will also let the house of
        Israel inquire of Me to do this for them: I will increase their men like
        a flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Like a flock offered  as holy sacrifices, like the flock at Jerusalem
        on its feast days, so shall the ruined cities be filled with flocks of men.
        Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dry Bones Live'
      title: The Dry Bones Live
      number: 1
      content: 'The hand of the Lord came upon me and brought me out in the Spirit
        of the Lord, and set me down in the midst of the valley; and it was full
        of bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then He caused me to pass by them all around, and behold, there 
        were very many in the open valley; and indeed they  were very dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CSon of man, can these bones live?\u201DSo
        I answered, \u201CO Lord God, You know.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Again He said to me, \u201CProphesy to these bones, and say to them,
        \u2018O dry bones, hear the word of the Lord! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord God to these bones: \u201CSurely I will cause
        breath to enter into you, and you shall live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will put sinews on you and bring flesh upon you, cover you with
        skin and put breath in you; and you shall live. Then you shall know that
        I am the Lord.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I prophesied as I was commanded; and as I prophesied, there was
        a noise, and suddenly a rattling; and the bones came together, bone to bone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Indeed, as I looked, the sinews and the flesh came upon them, and
        the skin covered them over; but there  was no breath in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Also He said to me, \u201CProphesy to the breath, prophesy, son of
        man, and say to the breath, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CCome from
        the four winds, O breath, and breathe on these slain, that they may live.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So I prophesied as He commanded me, and breath came into them, and
        they lived, and stood upon their feet, an exceedingly great army.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then He said to me, \u201CSon of man, these bones are the whole house
        of Israel. They indeed say, \u2018Our bones are dry, our hope is lost, and
        we ourselves are cut off!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore prophesy and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God:
        \u201CBehold, O My people, I will open your graves and cause you to come
        up from your graves, and bring you into the land of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you shall know that I am the Lord, when I have opened your graves,
        O My people, and brought you up from your graves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: One Kingdom, One King'
      title: One Kingdom, One King
      number: 14
      content: "I will put My Spirit in you, and you shall live, and I will place
        you in your own land. Then you shall know that I, the Lord, have spoken it
        and performed it,\u201D says the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAs for you, son of man, take a stick for yourself and write
        on it: \u2018For Judah and for the children of Israel, his companions.\u2019
        Then take another stick and write on it, \u2018For Joseph, the stick of Ephraim,
        and for all the house of Israel, his companions.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then join them one to another for yourself into one stick, and they
        will become one in your hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd when the children of your people speak to you, saying,
        \u2018Will you not show us what you mean by these?\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CSurely I will take
        the stick of Joseph, which is in the hand of Ephraim, and the tribes of Israel,
        his companions; and I will join them with it, with the stick of Judah, and
        make them one stick, and they will be one in My hand.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And the sticks on which you write will be in your hand before their
        eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThen say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CSurely
        I will take the children of Israel from among the nations, wherever they
        have gone, and will gather them from every side and bring them into their
        own land; "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and I will make them one nation in the land, on the mountains of
        Israel; and one king shall be king over them all; they shall no longer be
        two nations, nor shall they ever be divided into two kingdoms again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They shall not defile themselves anymore with their idols, nor with
        their detestable things, nor with any of their transgressions; but I will
        deliver them from all their dwelling places in which they have sinned, and
        will cleanse them. Then they shall be My people, and I will be their God.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CDavid My servant shall  be king over them, and they shall all
        have one shepherd; they shall also walk in My judgments and observe My statutes,
        and do them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then they shall dwell in the land that I have given to Jacob My servant,
        where your fathers dwelt; and they shall dwell there, they, their children,
        and their children\u2019s children, forever; and My servant David shall 
        be their prince forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Moreover I will make a covenant of peace with them, and it shall
        be an everlasting covenant with them; I will establish them and multiply
        them, and I will set My sanctuary in their midst forevermore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'My tabernacle also shall be with them; indeed I will be their God,
        and they shall be My people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The nations also will know that I, the Lord, sanctify Israel, when
        My sanctuary is in their midst forevermore.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gog and Allies Attack Israel'
      title: Gog and Allies Attack Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSon of man, set your face against Gog, of the land of Magog,
        the prince of Rosh, Meshech, and Tubal, and prophesy against him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord God: Behold, I am against you,
        O Gog, the prince of Rosh, Meshech, and Tubal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will turn you around, put hooks into your jaws, and lead you out,
        with all your army, horses, and horsemen, all splendidly clothed, a great
        company with bucklers and shields, all of them handling swords. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Persia, Ethiopia, and Libya are with them, all of them with shield
        and helmet; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Gomer and all its troops; the house of Togarmah from the far north
        and all its troops\u2014many people are with you."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CPrepare yourself and be ready, you and all your companies that
        are gathered about you; and be a guard for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After many days you will be visited. In the latter years you will
        come into the land of those brought back from the sword and gathered from
        many people on the mountains of Israel, which had long been desolate; they
        were brought out of the nations, and now all of them dwell safely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You will ascend, coming like a storm, covering the land like a cloud,
        you and all your troops and many peoples with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201COn that day it shall come to
        pass that thoughts will arise in your mind, and you will make an evil plan: "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "You will say, \u2018I will go up against a land of unwalled villages;
        I will go to a peaceful people, who dwell safely, all of them dwelling without
        walls, and having neither bars nor gates\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'to take plunder and to take booty, to stretch out your hand against
        the waste places that  are  again inhabited, and against a people gathered
        from the nations, who have acquired livestock and goods, who dwell in the
        midst of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Sheba, Dedan, the merchants of Tarshish, and all their young lions
        will say to you, \u2018Have you come to take plunder? Have you gathered your
        army to take booty, to carry away silver and gold, to take away livestock
        and goods, to take great plunder?\u2019 \u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore, son of man, prophesy and say to Gog, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord God: \u201COn that day when My people Israel dwell safely,
        will you not know it?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then you will come from your place out of the far north, you and
        many peoples with you, all of them riding on horses, a great company and
        a mighty army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You will come up against My people Israel like a cloud, to cover
        the land. It will be in the latter days that I will bring you against My
        land, so that the nations may know Me, when I am hallowed in you, O Gog,
        before their eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Judgment on Gog'
      title: Judgment on Gog
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CAre you he of whom I have spoken in
        former days by My servants the prophets of Israel, who prophesied for years
        in those days that I would bring you against them?"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd it will come to pass at the same time, when Gog comes against
        the land of Israel,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cthat My fury will show
        in My face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For in My jealousy and in the fire of My wrath I have spoken: \u2018Surely
        in that day there shall be a great earthquake in the land of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "so that the fish of the sea, the birds of the heavens, the beasts
        of the field, all creeping things that creep on the earth, and all men who
        are on the face of the earth shall shake at My presence. The mountains shall
        be thrown down, the steep places shall fall, and every wall shall fall to
        the ground.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will call for a sword against Gog throughout all My mountains,\u201D
        says the Lord God. \u201CEvery man\u2019s sword will be against his brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I will bring him to judgment with pestilence and bloodshed; I
        will rain down on him, on his troops, and on the many peoples who are with
        him, flooding rain, great hailstones, fire, and brimstone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus I will magnify Myself and sanctify Myself, and I will be known
        in the eyes of many nations. Then they shall know that I am the Lord.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Gog\u2019s Armies Destroyed"
      title: "Gog\u2019s Armies Destroyed"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAnd you, son of man, prophesy against Gog, and say, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord God: \u201CBehold, I am against you, O Gog, the prince of Rosh,
        Meshech, and Tubal; "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and I will turn you around and lead you on, bringing you up from
        the far north, and bring you against the mountains of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I will knock the bow out of your left hand, and cause the arrows
        to fall out of your right hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall fall upon the mountains of Israel, you and all your troops
        and the peoples who are with you; I will give you to birds of prey of every
        sort and to the beasts of the field to be devoured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You shall fall on the open field; for I have spoken,\u201D says the
        Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd I will send fire on Magog and on those who live in security
        in the coastlands. Then they shall know that I am the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I will make My holy name known in the midst of My people Israel,
        and I will not let  them  profane My holy name anymore. Then the nations
        shall know that I  am the Lord, the Holy One in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Surely it is coming, and it shall be done,\u201D says the Lord God.
        \u201CThis is the day of which I have spoken."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThen those who dwell in the cities of Israel will go out and
        set on fire and burn the weapons, both the shields and bucklers, the bows
        and arrows, the javelins and spears; and they will make fires with them for
        seven years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Burial of Gog'
      title: The Burial of Gog
      number: 10
      content: "They will not take wood from the field nor cut down any from the
        forests, because they will make fires with the weapons; and they will plunder
        those who plundered them, and pillage those who pillaged them,\u201D says
        the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIt will come to pass in that day that I will give Gog a burial
        place there in Israel, the valley of those who pass by east of the sea; and
        it will obstruct travelers, because there they will bury Gog and all his
        multitude. Therefore they will call it the Valley of Hamon Gog. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For seven months the house of Israel will be burying them, in order
        to cleanse the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Indeed all the people of the land will be burying, and they will
        gain renown for it on the day that I am glorified,\u201D says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThey will set apart men regularly employed, with the help of
        a search party, to pass through the land and bury those bodies remaining
        on the ground, in order to cleanse it. At the end of seven months they will
        make a search. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The search party will pass through the land; and when  anyone sees
        a man\u2019s bone, he shall set up a marker by it, till the buriers have
        buried it in the Valley of Hamon Gog. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: A Triumphant Festival'
      title: A Triumphant Festival
      number: 16
      content: "The name of the city will also be Hamonah. Thus they shall cleanse
        the land.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd as for you, son of man, thus says the Lord God, \u2018Speak
        to every sort of bird and to every beast of the field:\u201CAssemble yourselves
        and come;Gather together from all sides to My sacrificial mealWhich I am
        sacrificing for you,A great sacrificial meal on the mountains of Israel,That
        you may eat flesh and drink blood."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: You shall eat the flesh of the mighty,Drink the blood of the princes
        of the earth,Of rams and lambs,Of goats and bulls,All of them fatlings of
        Bashan.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: You shall eat fat till you are full,And drink blood till you are drunk,At
        My sacrificial mealWhich I am sacrificing for you.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Israel Restored to the Land'
      title: Israel Restored to the Land
      number: 20
      content: "You shall be filled at My tableWith horses and riders,With mighty
        menAnd with all the men of war,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI will set My glory among the nations; all the nations shall
        see My judgment which I have executed, and My hand which I have laid on them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the house of Israel shall know that I am the Lord their God from
        that day forward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The Gentiles shall know that the house of Israel went into captivity
        for their iniquity; because they were unfaithful to Me, therefore I hid My
        face from them. I gave them into the hand of their enemies, and they all
        fell by the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "According to their uncleanness and according to their transgressions
        I have dealt with them, and hidden My face from them.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God: \u2018Now I will bring back
        the captives of Jacob, and have mercy on the whole house of Israel; and I
        will be jealous for My holy name\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'after they have borne their shame, and all their unfaithfulness in
        which they were unfaithful to Me, when they dwelt safely in their own land
        and no one made them afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When I have brought them back from the peoples and gathered them
        out of their enemies\u2019 lands, and I am hallowed in them in the sight
        of many nations, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'then they shall know that I am the Lord their God, who sent them
        into captivity among the nations, but also brought them back to their land,
        and left none of them captive any longer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And I will not hide My face from them anymore; for I shall have poured
        out My Spirit on the house of Israel,\u2019 says the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A New City, a New Temple'
      title: A New City, a New Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twenty-fifth year of our captivity, at the beginning of the
        year, on the tenth day of the month, in the fourteenth year after the city
        was captured, on the very same day the hand of the Lord was upon me; and
        He took me there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the visions of God He took me into the land of Israel and set
        me on a very high mountain; on it toward the south was something like the
        structure of a city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He took me there, and behold, there  was a man whose appearance was 
        like the appearance of bronze. He had a line of flax and a measuring rod
        in his hand, and he stood in the gateway.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the man said to me, \u201CSon of man, look with your eyes and
        hear with your ears, and fix your mind on everything I show you; for you
        were brought here so that I might show them to you. Declare to the house
        of Israel everything you see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Eastern Gateway of the Temple'
      title: The Eastern Gateway of the Temple
      number: 5
      content: "Now there was a wall all around the outside of the temple. In the
        man\u2019s hand was a measuring rod six cubits long, each being a cubit and
        a handbreadth; and he measured the width of the wall structure, one rod;
        and the height, one rod."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he went to the gateway which faced east; and he went up its
        stairs and measured the threshold of the gateway, which  was one rod wide,
        and the other threshold was one rod wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Each gate chamber was one rod long and one rod wide; between the
        gate chambers was  a  space  of five cubits; and the threshold of the gateway
        by the vestibule of the inside gate was one rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He also measured the vestibule of the inside gate, one rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then he measured the vestibule of the gateway, eight cubits; and
        the gateposts, two cubits. The vestibule of the gate was on the inside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: In the eastern gateway were three gate chambers on one side and three
        on the other; the three were all the same size; also the gateposts were of
        the same size on this side and that side.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He measured the width of the entrance to the gateway, ten cubits;
        and the length of the gate, thirteen cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There  was a space in front of the gate chambers, one cubit on  this 
        side and one cubit on that side; the gate chambers were six cubits on this
        side and six cubits on that side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then he measured the gateway from the roof of one gate chamber to
        the roof of the other; the width was twenty-five cubits, as door faces door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He measured the gateposts, sixty cubits high, and the court all around
        the gateway extended to the gatepost. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'From the front of the entrance gate to the front of the vestibule
        of the inner gate was fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Outer Court'
      title: The Outer Court
      number: 16
      content: There  were  beveled window frames in the gate chambers and in their
        intervening archways on the inside of the gateway all around, and likewise
        in the vestibules. There  were windows all around on the inside. And on each
        gatepost were  palm trees.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he brought me into the outer court; and there  were  chambers
        and a pavement made all around the court; thirty chambers faced the pavement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The pavement was by the side of the gateways, corresponding to the
        length of the gateways; this  was the lower pavement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Northern Gateway'
      title: The Northern Gateway
      number: 19
      content: Then he measured the width from the front of the lower gateway to
        the front of the inner court exterior, one hundred cubits toward the east
        and the north.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'On the outer court was also a gateway facing north, and he measured
        its length and its width. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Its gate chambers, three on this side and three on that side, its
        gateposts and its archways, had the same measurements as the first gate;
        its length was fifty cubits and its width twenty-five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Its windows and those of its archways, and also its palm trees, had
        the same measurements as the gateway facing east; it was ascended by seven
        steps, and its archway was in front of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Southern Gateway'
      title: The Southern Gateway
      number: 23
      content: A gate of the inner court was opposite the northern gateway, just
        as the eastern gateway; and he measured from gateway to gateway, one hundred
        cubits.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After that he brought me toward the south, and there a gateway was
        facing south; and he measured its gateposts and archways according to these
        same measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There  were windows in it and in its archways all around like those
        windows; its length was fifty cubits and its width twenty-five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Seven steps led up to it, and its archway was in front of them; and
        it had palm trees on its gateposts, one on this side and one on that side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Gateways of the Inner Court'
      title: Gateways of the Inner Court
      number: 27
      content: There  was also a gateway on the inner court, facing south; and he
        measured from gateway to gateway toward the south, one hundred cubits.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he brought me to the inner court through the southern gateway;
        he measured the southern gateway according to these same measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Also its gate chambers, its gateposts, and its archways were according
        to these same measurements; there  were windows in it and in its archways
        all around; it  was fifty cubits long and twenty-five cubits wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There  were archways all around, twenty-five cubits long and five
        cubits wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Its archways faced the outer court, palm trees were on its gateposts,
        and going up to it were eight steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he brought me into the inner court facing east; he measured the
        gateway according to these same measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Also its gate chambers, its gateposts, and its archways were according
        to these same measurements; and there  were windows in it and in its archways
        all around; it  was fifty cubits long and twenty-five cubits wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Its archways faced the outer court, and palm trees were on its gateposts
        on this side and on that side; and going up to it were eight steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then he brought me to the north gateway and measured it according
        to these same measurements\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'also its gate chambers, its gateposts, and its archways. It had windows
        all around; its length was fifty cubits and its width twenty-five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Where Sacrifices Were Prepared'
      title: Where Sacrifices Were Prepared
      number: 37
      content: Its gateposts faced the outer court, palm trees were on its gateposts
        on this side and on that side, and going up to it were eight steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'There  was a chamber and its entrance by the gateposts of the gateway,
        where they washed the burnt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'In the vestibule of the gateway were two tables on this side and
        two tables on that side, on which to slay the burnt offering, the sin offering,
        and the trespass offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'At the outer side of the vestibule, as one goes up to the entrance
        of the northern gateway, were two tables; and on the other side of the vestibule
        of the gateway were two tables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Four tables were on this side and four tables on that side, by the
        side of the gateway, eight tables on which they slaughtered the  sacrifices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'There  were also four tables of hewn stone for the burnt offering,
        one cubit and a half long, one cubit and a half wide, and one cubit high;
        on these they laid the instruments with which they slaughtered the burnt
        offering and the sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Chambers for Singers and Priests'
      title: Chambers for Singers and Priests
      number: 43
      content: Inside were hooks, a handbreadth wide, fastened all around; and the
        flesh of the sacrifices was on the tables.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Outside the inner gate were the chambers for the singers in the inner
        court, one facing south at the side of the northern gateway, and the other
        facing north at the side of the southern gateway. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis chamber which faces south is for the
        priests who have charge of the temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Dimensions of the Inner Court and Vestibule'
      title: Dimensions of the Inner Court and Vestibule
      number: 46
      content: "The chamber which faces north is for the priests who have charge
        of the altar; these are the sons of Zadok, from the sons of Levi, who come
        near the Lord to minister to Him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And he measured the court, one hundred cubits long and one hundred
        cubits wide, foursquare. The altar was in front of the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Then he brought me to the vestibule of the temple and measured the
        doorposts of the vestibule, five cubits on this side and five cubits on that
        side; and the width of the gateway was three cubits on this side and three
        cubits on that side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: The length of the vestibule was twenty cubits, and the width eleven
        cubits; and by the steps which led up to it there  were  pillars by the doorposts,
        one on this side and another on that side.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Dimensions of the Sanctuary'
      title: Dimensions of the Sanctuary
      number: 1
      content: "Then he brought me into the sanctuary and measured the doorposts,
        six cubits wide on one side and six cubits wide on the other side\u2014the
        width of the tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The width of the entryway was ten cubits, and the side walls of the
        entrance were five cubits on this side and five cubits on the other side;
        and he measured its length, forty cubits, and its width, twenty cubits.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Also he went inside and measured the doorposts, two cubits; and the
        entrance, six cubits high; and the width of the entrance, seven cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Side Chambers on the Wall'
      title: The Side Chambers on the Wall
      number: 4
      content: "He measured the length, twenty cubits; and the width, twenty cubits,
        beyond the sanctuary; and he said to me, \u201CThis is the Most Holy Place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Next, he measured the wall of the temple, six cubits. The width of
        each side chamber all around the temple was four cubits on every side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The side chambers were in three stories, one above the other, thirty
        chambers in each story; they rested on ledges which were for the side chambers
        all around, that they might be supported, but not fastened to the wall of
        the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As one went up from story to story, the side chambers became wider
        all around, because their supporting ledges in the wall of the temple ascended
        like steps; therefore the width of the structure increased as one went up
        from the lowest story to the highest by way of the middle one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I also saw an elevation all around the temple; it was the foundation
        of the side chambers, a full rod, that  is, six cubits high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The thickness of the outer wall of the side chambers was five cubits,
        and so also the remaining terrace by the place of the side chambers of the
        temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And between it  and the wall chambers was a width of twenty cubits
        all around the temple on every side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Building at the Western End'
      title: The Building at the Western End
      number: 11
      content: The doors of the side chambers opened on the terrace, one door toward
        the north and another toward the south; and the width of the terrace was
        five cubits all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Dimensions and Design of the Temple Area'
      title: Dimensions and Design of the Temple Area
      number: 12
      content: The building that faced the separating courtyard at its western end
        was seventy cubits wide; the wall of the building was five cubits thick all
        around, and its length ninety cubits.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he measured the temple, one hundred cubits long; and the separating
        courtyard with the building and its walls was one hundred cubits long; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'also the width of the eastern face of the temple, including the separating
        courtyard, was one hundred cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He measured the length of the building behind it, facing the separating
        courtyard, with its galleries on the one side and on the other side, one
        hundred cubits, as well as the inner temple and the porches of the court, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "their doorposts and the beveled window frames. And the galleries
        all around their three stories opposite the threshold were paneled with wood
        from the ground to the windows\u2014the windows were covered\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: from the space above the door, even to the inner room, as well as
        outside, and on every wall all around, inside and outside, by measure.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And it  was made with cherubim and palm trees, a palm tree between
        cherub and cherub. Each cherub had two faces, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'so that the face of a man was toward a palm tree on one side, and
        the face of a young lion toward a palm tree on the other side; thus it  was
        made throughout the temple all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: From the floor to the space above the door, and on the wall of the
        sanctuary, cherubim and palm trees were carved.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The doorposts of the temple were square, as  was the front of the
        sanctuary; their appearance was similar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The altar was of wood, three cubits high, and its length two cubits.
        Its corners, its length, and its sides were of wood; and he said to me, \u201CThis
        is  the table that is  before the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The temple and the sanctuary had two doors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The doors had two panels apiece, two folding panels: two panels for
        one door and two panels for the other door.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Cherubim and palm trees were carved on the doors of the temple just
        as they were carved on the walls. A wooden canopy was on the front of the
        vestibule outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "There  were  beveled window frames and palm trees on one side and
        on the other, on the sides of the vestibule\u2014also on the side chambers
        of the temple and on the canopies."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Chambers for the Priests'
      title: The Chambers for the Priests
      number: 1
      content: 'Then he brought me out into the outer court, by the way toward the
        north; and he brought me into the chamber which was opposite the separating
        courtyard, and which was opposite the building toward the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Facing the length, which  was one hundred cubits (the width was fifty
        cubits), was the north door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Opposite the inner court of twenty cubits, and opposite the pavement
        of the outer court, was  gallery against gallery in three stories.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In front of the chambers, toward the inside, was a walk ten cubits
        wide, at a distance of one cubit; and their doors faced north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the upper chambers were shorter, because the galleries took away
        space from them more than from the lower and middle stories of the building. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For they were in three stories and did not have pillars like the
        pillars of the courts; therefore the  upper  level was shortened more than
        the lower and middle levels from the ground up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And a wall which was outside ran parallel to the chambers, at the
        front of the chambers, toward the outer court; its length was fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The length of the chambers toward the outer court was fifty cubits,
        whereas that facing the temple was one hundred cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: At the lower chambers was the entrance on the east side, as one goes
        into them from the outer court.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also there  were chambers in the thickness of the wall of the court
        toward the east, opposite the separating courtyard and opposite the building. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There  was a walk in front of them also, and their appearance was
        like the chambers which were toward the north; they were as long and as wide
        as the others, and all their exits and entrances were according to plan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And corresponding to the doors of the chambers that were facing south,
        as one enters them, there  was a door in front of the walk, the way directly
        in front of the wall toward the east.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThe north chambers and the south chambers,
        which are opposite the separating courtyard, are the holy chambers where
        the priests who approach the Lord  shall eat the most holy offerings. There
        they shall lay the most holy offerings\u2014the grain offering, the sin offering,
        and the trespass offering\u2014for the place is holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Outer Dimensions of the Temple'
      title: Outer Dimensions of the Temple
      number: 14
      content: "When the priests enter them, they shall not go out of the holy chamber
        into the outer court; but there they shall leave their garments in which
        they minister, for they are holy. They shall put on other garments; then
        they may approach that which is for the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now when he had finished measuring the inner temple, he brought me
        out through the gateway that faces toward the east, and measured it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He measured the east side with the measuring rod, five hundred rods
        by the measuring rod all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He measured the north side, five hundred rods by the measuring rod
        all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He measured the south side, five hundred rods by the measuring rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He came around to the west side and measured five hundred rods by
        the measuring rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He measured it on the four sides; it had a wall all around, five hundred
        cubits long and five hundred wide, to separate the holy areas from the common.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Temple, the Lord\u2019s Dwelling Place"
      title: "The Temple, the Lord\u2019s Dwelling Place"
      number: 1
      content: 'Afterward he brought me to the gate, the gate that faces toward the
        east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And behold, the glory of the God of Israel came from the way of the
        east. His voice was like the sound of many waters; and the earth shone with
        His glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It  was  like the appearance of the vision which I saw\u2014like
        the vision which I saw when I came to destroy the city. The visions were
        like the vision which I saw by the River Chebar; and I fell on my face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the glory of the Lord came into the temple by way of the gate
        which faces toward the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Spirit lifted me up and brought me into the inner court; and behold,
        the glory of the Lord filled the temple.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then I heard Him speaking to me from the temple, while a man stood
        beside me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CSon of man, this  is  the place of My throne
        and the place of the soles of My feet, where I will dwell in the midst of
        the children of Israel forever. No more shall the house of Israel defile
        My holy name, they nor their kings, by their harlotry or with the carcasses
        of their kings on their high places. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When they set their threshold by My threshold, and their doorpost
        by My doorpost, with a wall between them and Me, they defiled My holy name
        by the abominations which they committed; therefore I have consumed them
        in My anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Now let them put their harlotry and the carcasses of their kings far
        away from Me, and I will dwell in their midst forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSon of man, describe the temple to the house of Israel, that
        they may be ashamed of their iniquities; and let them measure the pattern. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And if they are ashamed of all that they have done, make known to
        them the design of the temple and its arrangement, its exits and its entrances,
        its entire design and all its ordinances, all its forms and all its laws.
        Write it down in their sight, so that they may keep its whole design and
        all its ordinances, and perform them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Dimensions of the Altar'
      title: Dimensions of the Altar
      number: 12
      content: 'This is the law of the temple: The whole area surrounding the mountaintop
        is most holy. Behold, this is the law of the temple.'
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThese are the measurements of the altar in cubits (the cubit
        is one cubit and a handbreadth): the base one cubit high and one cubit wide,
        with a rim all around its edge of one span. This is the height of the altar: "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'from the base on the ground to the lower ledge, two cubits; the width
        of the ledge, one cubit; from the smaller ledge to the larger ledge, four
        cubits; and the width of the ledge, one cubit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The altar hearth is four cubits high, with four horns extending upward
        from the hearth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The altar hearth is twelve cubits long, twelve wide, square at its
        four corners; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Consecrating the Altar'
      title: Consecrating the Altar
      number: 17
      content: "the ledge, fourteen cubits long and fourteen wide on its four sides,
        with a rim of half a cubit around it; its base, one cubit all around; and
        its steps face toward the east.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And He said to me, \u201CSon of man, thus says the Lord God: \u2018These
        are the ordinances for the altar on the day when it is made, for sacrificing
        burnt offerings on it, and for sprinkling blood on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You shall give a young bull for a sin offering to the priests, the
        Levites, who are of the seed of Zadok, who approach Me to minister to Me,\u2019
        says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018You shall take some of its blood and put it on the four horns
        of the altar, on the four corners of the ledge, and on the rim around it;
        thus you shall cleanse it and make atonement for it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then you shall also take the bull of the sin offering, and burn it
        in the appointed place of the temple, outside the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On the second day you shall offer a kid of the goats without blemish
        for a sin offering; and they shall cleanse the altar, as they cleansed it
        with the bull. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When you have finished cleansing it, you shall offer a young bull
        without blemish, and a ram from the flock without blemish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When you offer them before the Lord, the priests shall throw salt
        on them, and they will offer them up as a burnt offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Every day for seven days you shall prepare a goat for a sin offering;
        they shall also prepare a young bull and a ram from the flock, both without
        blemish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Seven days they shall make atonement for the altar and purify it,
        and so consecrate it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When these days are over it shall be, on the eighth day and thereafter,
        that the priests shall offer your burnt offerings and your peace offerings
        on the altar; and I will accept you,\u2019 says the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The East Gate and the Prince'
      title: The East Gate and the Prince
      number: 1
      content: 'Then He brought me back to the outer gate of the sanctuary which
        faces toward the east, but it was shut. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CThis gate shall be shut; it shall
        not be opened, and no man shall enter by it, because the Lord God of Israel
        has entered by it; therefore it shall be shut. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Those Admitted to the Temple'
      title: Those Admitted to the Temple
      number: 3
      content: "As  for the prince, because he is the prince, he may sit in it to
        eat bread before the Lord; he shall enter by way of the vestibule of the
        gateway, and go out the same way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Also He brought me by way of the north gate to the front of the temple;
        so I looked, and behold, the glory of the Lord filled the house of the Lord;
        and I fell on my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CSon of man, mark well, see with your
        eyes and hear with your ears, all that I say to you concerning all the ordinances
        of the house of the Lord and all its laws. Mark well who may enter the house
        and all who go out from the sanctuary."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNow say to the rebellious, to the house of Israel, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord God: \u201CO house of Israel, let Us have no more of all your
        abominations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When you brought in foreigners, uncircumcised in heart and uncircumcised
        in flesh, to be in My sanctuary to defile it\u2014My house\u2014and when
        you offered My food, the fat and the blood, then they broke My covenant because
        of all your abominations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And you have not kept charge of My holy things, but you have set
        others to keep charge of My sanctuary for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Laws Governing Priests'
      title: Laws Governing Priests
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CNo foreigner, uncircumcised in heart
        or uncircumcised in flesh, shall enter My sanctuary, including any foreigner
        who is among the children of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd the Levites who went far from Me, when Israel went astray,
        who strayed away from Me after their idols, they shall bear their iniquity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yet they shall be ministers in My sanctuary, as gatekeepers of the
        house and ministers of the house; they shall slay the burnt offering and
        the sacrifice for the people, and they shall stand before them to minister
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Because they ministered to them before their idols and caused the
        house of Israel to fall into iniquity, therefore I have raised My hand in
        an oath against them,\u201D says the Lord God, \u201Cthat they shall bear
        their iniquity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And they shall not come near Me to minister to Me as priest, nor
        come near any of My holy things, nor into the Most Holy Place; but they shall
        bear their shame and their abominations which they have committed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Nevertheless I will make them keep charge of the temple, for all its
        work, and for all that has to be done in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut the priests, the Levites, the sons of Zadok, who kept charge
        of My sanctuary when the children of Israel went astray from Me, they shall
        come near Me to minister to Me; and they shall stand before Me to offer to
        Me the fat and the blood,\u201D says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThey shall enter My sanctuary, and they shall come near My
        table to minister to Me, and they shall keep My charge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it shall be, whenever they enter the gates of the inner court,
        that they shall put on linen garments; no wool shall come upon them while
        they minister within the gates of the inner court or within the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They shall have linen turbans on their heads and linen trousers on
        their bodies; they shall not clothe themselves with anything  that  causes
        sweat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: When they go out to the outer court, to the outer court to the people,
        they shall take off their garments in which they have ministered, leave them
        in the holy chambers, and put on other garments; and in their holy garments
        they shall not sanctify the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThey shall neither shave their heads nor let their hair grow
        long, but they shall keep their hair well trimmed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'No priest shall drink wine when he enters the inner court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: They shall not take as wife a widow or a divorced woman, but take
        virgins of the descendants of the house of Israel, or widows of priests.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd they shall teach My people the  difference between the
        holy and the unholy, and cause them to discern between the unclean and the
        clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: In controversy they shall stand as judges, and judge it according
        to My judgments. They shall keep My laws and My statutes in all My appointed
        meetings, and they shall hallow My Sabbaths.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThey shall not defile themselves by coming near a dead person.
        Only for father or mother, for son or daughter, for brother or unmarried
        sister may they defile themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'After he is cleansed, they shall count seven days for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And on the day that he goes to the sanctuary to minister in the sanctuary,
        he must offer his sin offering in the inner court,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIt shall be, in regard to their inheritance, that I am their
        inheritance. You shall give them no possession in Israel, for I am their
        possession. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They shall eat the grain offering, the sin offering, and the trespass
        offering; every dedicated thing in Israel shall be theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The best of all firstfruits of any kind, and every sacrifice of any
        kind from all your sacrifices, shall be the priest\u2019s; also you shall
        give to the priest the first of your ground meal, to cause a blessing to
        rest on your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The priests shall not eat anything, bird or beast, that died naturally
        or was torn by  wild  beasts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Holy District'
      title: The Holy District
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMoreover, when you divide the land by lot into inheritance,
        you shall set apart a district for the Lord, a holy section of the land;
        its length shall  be twenty-five thousand cubits, and the width ten thousand.
        It shall  be holy throughout its territory all around. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Of this there shall be a square plot for the sanctuary, five hundred
        by five hundred rods, with fifty cubits around it for an open space. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So this is the district you shall measure: twenty-five thousand cubits
        long and ten thousand wide; in it shall be the sanctuary, the Most Holy Place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It shall be a holy section of the land, belonging to the priests,
        the ministers of the sanctuary, who come near to minister to the Lord; it
        shall be a place for their houses and a holy place for the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Properties of the City and the Prince'
      title: Properties of the City and the Prince
      number: 5
      content: An  area twenty-five thousand cubits long and ten thousand wide shall
        belong to the Levites, the ministers of the temple; they shall have twenty
        chambers as a possession.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou shall appoint as the property of the city an  area five
        thousand cubits wide and twenty-five thousand long, adjacent to the district
        of the holy section; it shall belong to the whole house of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe prince shall have a  section on one side and the other
        of the holy district and the city\u2019s property; and bordering on the holy
        district and the city\u2019s property, extending westward on the west side
        and eastward on the east side, the length shall  be side by side with one
        of the tribal portions, from the west border to the east border. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Laws Governing the Prince'
      title: Laws Governing the Prince
      number: 8
      content: "The land shall be his possession in Israel; and My princes shall
        no more oppress My people, but they shall give the  rest  of the land to
        the house of Israel, according to their tribes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CEnough, O princes of Israel!
        Remove violence and plundering, execute justice and righteousness, and stop
        dispossessing My people,\u201D says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall have honest scales, an honest ephah, and an honest
        bath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The ephah and the bath shall be of the same measure, so that the
        bath contains one-tenth of a homer, and the ephah one-tenth of a homer; their
        measure shall be according to the homer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The shekel shall  be twenty gerahs; twenty shekels, twenty-five shekels,
        and fifteen shekels shall be your mina.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis is the offering which you shall offer: you shall give
        one-sixth of an ephah from a homer of wheat, and one-sixth of an ephah from
        a homer of barley. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The ordinance concerning oil, the bath of oil, is one-tenth of a
        bath from a kor. A kor  is a homer or ten baths, for ten baths are a homer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And one lamb shall be given from a flock of two hundred, from the
        rich pastures of Israel. These shall be for grain offerings, burnt offerings,
        and peace offerings, to make atonement for them,\u201D says the Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAll the people of the land shall give this offering for the
        prince in Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Keeping the Feasts'
      title: Keeping the Feasts
      number: 17
      content: "Then it shall be the prince\u2019s part to  give burnt offerings,
        grain offerings, and drink offerings, at the feasts, the New Moons, the Sabbaths,
        and at all the appointed seasons of the house of Israel. He shall prepare
        the sin offering, the grain offering, the burnt offering, and the peace offerings
        to make atonement for the house of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CIn the first month, on the first
        day of the month, you shall take a young bull without blemish and cleanse
        the sanctuary. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering and put
        it on the doorposts of the temple, on the four corners of the ledge of the
        altar, and on the gateposts of the gate of the inner court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And so you shall do on the seventh day of the month for everyone who
        has sinned unintentionally or in ignorance. Thus you shall make atonement
        for the temple.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIn the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month, you
        shall observe the Passover, a feast of seven days; unleavened bread shall
        be eaten. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And on that day the prince shall prepare for himself and for all
        the people of the land a bull for a sin offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'On the seven days of the feast he shall prepare a burnt offering
        to the Lord, seven bulls and seven rams without blemish, daily for seven
        days, and a kid of the goats daily for a sin offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And he shall prepare a grain offering of one ephah for each bull and
        one ephah for each ram, together with a hin of oil for each ephah.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CIn the seventh month, on the fifteenth day of the month, at
        the feast, he shall do likewise for seven days, according to the sin offering,
        the burnt offering, the grain offering, and the oil.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Manner of Worship'
      title: The Manner of Worship
      number: 1
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CThe gateway of the inner court
        that faces toward the east shall be shut the six working days; but on the
        Sabbath it shall be opened, and on the day of the New Moon it shall be opened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The prince shall enter by way of the vestibule of the gateway from
        the outside, and stand by the gatepost. The priests shall prepare his burnt
        offering and his peace offerings. He shall worship at the threshold of the
        gate. Then he shall go out, but the gate shall not be shut until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Likewise the people of the land shall worship at the entrance to
        this gateway before the Lord on the Sabbaths and the New Moons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The burnt offering that the prince offers to the Lord on the Sabbath
        day shall  be six lambs without blemish, and a ram without blemish; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the grain offering shall  be  one ephah for a ram, and the grain
        offering for the lambs, as much as he wants to give, as well as a hin of
        oil with every ephah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the day of the New Moon it  shall  be a young bull without blemish,
        six lambs, and a ram; they shall be without blemish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He shall prepare a grain offering of an ephah for a bull, an ephah
        for a ram, as much as he wants to give for the lambs, and a hin of oil with
        every ephah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: When the prince enters, he shall go in by way of the vestibule of
        the gateway, and go out the same way.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBut when the people of the land come before the Lord on the
        appointed feast days, whoever enters by way of the north gate to worship
        shall go out by way of the south gate; and whoever enters by way of the south
        gate shall go out by way of the north gate. He shall not return by way of
        the gate through which he came, but shall go out through the opposite gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The prince shall then be in their midst. When they go in, he shall
        go in; and when they go out, he shall go out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: At the festivals and the appointed feast days the grain offering shall
        be an ephah for a bull, an ephah for a ram, as much as he wants to give for
        the lambs, and a hin of oil with every ephah.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CNow when the prince makes a voluntary burnt offering or voluntary
        peace offering to the Lord, the gate that faces toward the east shall then
        be opened for him; and he shall prepare his burnt offering and his peace
        offerings as he did on the Sabbath day. Then he shall go out, and after he
        goes out the gate shall be shut."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall daily make a burnt offering to the Lord  of a lamb
        of the first year without blemish; you shall prepare it every morning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And you shall prepare a grain offering with it every morning, a sixth
        of an ephah, and a third of a hin of oil to moisten the fine flour. This
        grain offering is a perpetual ordinance, to be made regularly to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Prince and Inheritance Laws'
      title: The Prince and Inheritance Laws
      number: 15
      content: "Thus they shall prepare the lamb, the grain offering, and the oil,
        as a regular burnt offering every morning.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God: \u201CIf the prince gives a gift of 
        some of his inheritance to any of his sons, it shall belong to his sons;
        it is their possession by inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But if he gives a gift of some of his inheritance to one of his servants,
        it shall be his until the year of liberty, after which it shall return to
        the prince. But his inheritance shall belong to his sons; it shall become
        theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: How the Offerings Were Prepared'
      title: How the Offerings Were Prepared
      number: 18
      content: "Moreover the prince shall not take any of the people\u2019s inheritance
        by evicting them from their property; he shall provide an inheritance for
        his sons from his own property, so that none of My people may be scattered
        from his property.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now he brought me through the entrance, which was at the side of
        the gate, into the holy chambers of the priests which face toward the north;
        and there a place was situated at their extreme western end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CThis is the place where the priests shall
        boil the trespass offering and the sin offering, and where they shall bake
        the grain offering, so that they do not bring them out into the outer court
        to sanctify the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then he brought me out into the outer court and caused me to pass
        by the four corners of the court; and in fact, in every corner of the court
        there  was  another court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In the four corners of the court were enclosed courts, forty cubits
        long and thirty wide; all four corners were the same size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'There  was a row of  building  stones all around in them, all around
        the four of them; and cooking hearths were made under the rows of stones
        all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CThese are the kitchens where the ministers
        of the temple shall boil the sacrifices of the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Healing Waters and Trees'
      title: The Healing Waters and Trees
      number: 1
      content: 'Then he brought me back to the door of the temple; and there was
        water, flowing from under the threshold of the temple toward the east, for
        the front of the temple faced east; the water was flowing from under the
        right side of the temple, south of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He brought me out by way of the north gate, and led me around on the
        outside to the outer gateway that faces east; and there was water, running
        out on the right side.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when the man went out to the east with the line in his hand,
        he measured one thousand cubits, and he brought me through the waters; the
        water came  up  to  my ankles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Again he measured one thousand and brought me through the waters;
        the water came  up  to  my knees. Again he measured one thousand and brought
        me through; the water came  up  to  my waist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Again he measured one thousand, and  it  was a river that I could
        not cross; for the water was too deep, water in which one must swim, a river
        that could not be crossed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to me, \u201CSon of man, have you seen this?\u201D Then he
        brought me and returned me to the bank of the river."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When I returned, there, along the bank of the river, were very many
        trees on one side and the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said to me: \u201CThis water flows toward the eastern region,
        goes down into the valley, and enters the sea. When  it reaches the sea,
        its waters are healed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall be that every living thing that moves, wherever the
        rivers go, will live. There will be a very great multitude of fish, because
        these waters go there; for they will be healed, and everything will live
        wherever the river goes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'It shall be that fishermen will stand by it from En Gedi to En Eglaim;
        they will be places for spreading their nets. Their fish will be of the same
        kinds as the fish of the Great Sea, exceedingly many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But its swamps and marshes will not be healed; they will be given
        over to salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Borders of the Land'
      title: Borders of the Land
      number: 12
      content: "Along the bank of the river, on this side and that, will grow all
        kinds  of trees used for food; their leaves will not wither, and their fruit
        will not fail. They will bear fruit every month, because their water flows
        from the sanctuary. Their fruit will be for food, and their leaves for medicine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus says the Lord God: \u201CThese are the borders by which you
        shall divide the land as an inheritance among the twelve tribes of Israel.
        Joseph shall  have  two portions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You shall inherit it equally with one another; for I raised My hand
        in an oath to give it to your fathers, and this land shall fall to you as
        your inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThis shall  be the border of the land on the north: from the
        Great Sea, by  the road to Hethlon, as one goes to Zedad, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Hamath, Berothah, Sibraim (which is between the border of Damascus
        and the border of Hamath), to Hazar Hatticon (which is on the border of Hauran). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Thus the boundary shall be from the Sea to Hazar Enan, the border
        of Damascus; and as for the north, northward, it is the border of Hamath.
        This  is the north side.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201COn the east side you shall mark out the border from between
        Hauran and Damascus, and between Gilead and the land of Israel, along the
        Jordan, and along the eastern side of the sea. This  is the east side."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe south side, toward the South, shall  be from Tamar to the
        waters of Meribah by Kadesh, along the brook to the Great Sea. This  is the
        south side, toward the South."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe west side shall  be the Great Sea, from the southern boundary
        until one comes to a point opposite Hamath. This is the west side."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThus you shall divide this land among yourselves according
        to the tribes of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It shall be that you will divide it by lot as an inheritance for
        yourselves, and for the strangers who dwell among you and who bear children
        among you. They shall be to you as native-born among the children of Israel;
        they shall have an inheritance with you among the tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it shall be that in whatever tribe the stranger dwells, there
        you shall give him his inheritance,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Division of the Land'
      title: Division of the Land
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CNow these are the names of the tribes: From the northern border
        along the road to Hethlon at the entrance of Hamath, to Hazar Enan, the border
        of Damascus northward, in the direction of Hamath, there  shall  be one section 
        for  Dan from its east to its west side; "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'by the border of Dan, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Asher; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'by the border of Asher, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Naphtali; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'by the border of Naphtali, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Manasseh; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'by the border of Manasseh, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Ephraim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'by the border of Ephraim, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Reuben; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'by the border of Reuben, from the east side to the west, one section 
        for  Judah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: by the border of Judah, from the east side to the west, shall be the
        district which you shall set apart, twenty-five thousand cubits in width,
        and in length the same as one of the other portions, from the east side to
        the west, with the sanctuary in the center.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe district that you shall set apart for the Lord  shall 
        be twenty-five thousand cubits in length and ten thousand in width. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "To these\u2014to the priests\u2014the holy district shall belong:
        on the north twenty-five thousand cubits  in  length, on the west ten thousand
        in width, on the east ten thousand in width, and on the south twenty-five
        thousand in length. The sanctuary of the Lord shall be in the center. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It  shall  be for the priests of the sons of Zadok, who are sanctified,
        who have kept My charge, who did not go astray when the children of Israel
        went astray, as the Levites went astray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And this district of land that is set apart shall be to them a thing
        most holy by the border of the Levites.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201COpposite the border of the priests, the Levites shall  have 
        an  area twenty-five thousand cubits in length and ten thousand in width;
        its entire length shall  be twenty-five thousand and its width ten thousand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And they shall not sell or exchange any of it; they may not alienate
        this best part of the land, for it  is holy to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe five thousand cubits in width that remain, along the edge
        of the twenty-five thousand, shall be for general use by the city, for dwellings
        and common-land; and the city shall be in the center. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These shall  be its measurements: the north side four thousand five
        hundred cubits, the south side four thousand five hundred, the east side
        four thousand five hundred, and the west side four thousand five hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The common-land of the city shall be: to the north two hundred and
        fifty cubits, to the south two hundred and fifty, to the east two hundred
        and fifty, and to the west two hundred and fifty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The rest of the length, alongside the district of the holy section,
        shall be ten thousand cubits to the east and ten thousand to the west. It
        shall be adjacent to the district of the holy section, and its produce shall
        be food for the workers of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The workers of the city, from all the tribes of Israel, shall cultivate
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The entire district shall  be twenty-five thousand cubits by twenty-five
        thousand cubits, foursquare. You shall set apart the holy district with the
        property of the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe rest shall  belong to the prince, on one side and on the
        other of the holy district and of the city\u2019s property, next to the twenty-five
        thousand cubits of the holy district as far as the eastern border, and westward
        next to the twenty-five thousand as far as the western border, adjacent to
        the tribal portions; it  shall  belong to the prince. It shall be the holy
        district, and the sanctuary of the temple shall  be in the center. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Moreover, apart from the possession of the Levites and the possession
        of the city which  are in the midst of what belongs to the prince, the  area
        between the border of Judah and the border of Benjamin shall belong to the
        prince.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAs for the rest of the tribes, from the east side to the west,
        Benjamin shall  have one section;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'by the border of Benjamin, from the east side to the west, Simeon
        shall  have one section;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'by the border of Simeon, from the east side to the west, Issachar
        shall  have one section;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'by the border of Issachar, from the east side to the west, Zebulun
        shall  have one section;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'by the border of Zebulun, from the east side to the west, Gad shall 
        have one section;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'by the border of Gad, on the south side, toward the South, the border
        shall be from Tamar to  the waters of Meribah by Kadesh, along the brook
        to the Great Sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Gates of the City and Its Name'
      title: The Gates of the City and Its Name
      number: 29
      content: "This is the land which you shall divide by lot as an inheritance
        among the tribes of Israel, and these are their portions,\u201D says the
        Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThese are the exits of the city. On the north side, measuring
        four thousand five hundred cubits  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '(the gates of the city shall  be named after the tribes of Israel),
        the three gates northward: one gate for Reuben, one gate for Judah, and one
        gate for Levi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'on the east side, four thousand five hundred cubits, three gates:
        one gate for Joseph, one gate for Benjamin, and one gate for Dan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'on the south side, measuring four thousand five hundred cubits, three
        gates: one gate for Simeon, one gate for Issachar, and one gate for Zebulun; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'on the west side, four thousand five hundred cubits with their three
        gates: one gate for Gad, one gate for Asher, and one gate for Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "All the way around shall  be eighteen thousand cubits;  and the name
        of the city from that day shall  be:  THE LORD IS THERE.\u201D"
      comments: []
